{"active":false,"cklb_version":"1.0","evaluate-stig":{"version":"1.2604.2"},"has_path":true,"id":"ddbc169b-80d2-49f5-b108-7b482650654f","mode":1,"stigs":[{"evaluate-stig":{"time":"2026-07-23T17:12:42.0000000+00:00","module":{"name":"Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks","version":"1.2604.2"}},"stig_name":"Oracle Linux 9 Security Technical Implementation Guide","display_name":"Oracle Linux 9","stig_id":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG","release_info":"Release: 5 Benchmark Date: 01 Apr 2026","version":"1","uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","reference_identifier":"4728","size":448,"rules":[{"group_id_src":"V-271431","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271431","title":"SRG-OS-000780-GPOS-00240","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271431","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000780-GPOS-00240","rule_id_src":"SV-271431r1092616_rule","rule_id":"SV-271431","rule_version":"OL09-00-000001","rule_title":"The OL 9 operating system must implement cryptographic mechanisms to prevent unauthorized modification of all information at rest.","fix_text":"Configure the OL 9 operating system to implement cryptographic mechanisms to prevent unauthorized modification of all information at rest.\n\nTo encrypt an entire partition, dedicate a partition for encryption in the partition layout. \n \nNote: Encrypting a partition in an already-installed system is more difficult because it will need to be resized and existing partitions changed.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Note: If there is a documented and approved reason for not having data at rest encryption, this requirement is Not Applicable.\n\nVerify that OL 9 prevents unauthorized disclosure or modification of all information requiring at rest protection by using disk encryption.\n\nDetermine the partition layout for the system with the following command: \n \n$ sudo fdisk -l \n(..) \nDisk /dev/vda: 15 GiB, 16106127360 bytes, 31457280 sectors \nUnits: sectors of 1 * 512 = 512 bytes \nSector size (logical/physical): 512 bytes / 512 bytes \nI/O size (minimum/optimal): 512 bytes / 512 bytes \nDisklabel type: gpt \nDisk identifier: 83298450-B4E3-4B19-A9E4-7DF147A5FEFB \n \nDevice       Start      End  Sectors Size Type \n/dev/vda1     2048     4095     2048   1M BIOS boot \n/dev/vda2     4096  2101247  2097152   1G Linux filesystem \n/dev/vda3  2101248 31455231 29353984  14G Linux filesystem \n(...) \n \nVerify that the system partitions are all encrypted with the following command: \n \n$ sudo more /etc/crypttab \n \nEvery persistent disk partition present must have an entry in the file. \n \nIf any partitions other than the boot partition or pseudo file systems (such as /proc or /sys) are not listed, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Operating systems handling data requiring \"data at rest\" protections must employ cryptographic mechanisms to prevent unauthorized disclosure and modification of the information at rest. \n \nSelection of a cryptographic mechanism is based on the need to protect the integrity of organizational information. The strength of the mechanism is commensurate with the security category and/or classification of the information. Organizations have the flexibility to either encrypt all information on storage devices (i.e., full disk encryption) or encrypt specific data structures (e.g., files, records, or fields).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-004910"],"reference_identifier":"8259","uuid":"eccac209-223f-488d-8a1b-ad2b08b31090","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 31FB11861DA861792AA2A1663F3DDED2087A9D47\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The OL 9 operating system must implement cryptographic mechanisms to prevent unauthorized modification of all information at rest.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271432","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271432","title":"SRG-OS-000341-GPOS-00132","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271432","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000341-GPOS-00132","rule_id_src":"SV-271432r1091008_rule","rule_id":"SV-271432","rule_version":"OL09-00-000002","rule_title":"OL 9 must use a separate file system for the system audit data path.","fix_text":"Migrate the system audit data path onto a separate file system.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 uses a separate file system for the system audit data path with the following command:\n\nNote: /var/log/audit is used as the example as it is a common location.\n\n$ mount | grep /var/log/audit \nUUID=2efb2979-45ac-82d7-0ae632d11f51 on /var/log/home type xfs  (rw,realtime,seclabel,attr2,inode64)\n\nIf no line is returned, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Placing \"/var/log/audit\" in its own partition enables better separation between audit files and other system files and helps ensure that auditing cannot be halted due to the partition running out of space.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001849"],"reference_identifier":"5055","uuid":"06dc4906-af20-4b09-93eb-2a28e6ace8b1","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FF6197C0149FD05AE68AA9ED9F8489FC3EA74941\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'OL 9 must use a separate file system for the system audit data path.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271433","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271433","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271433","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-271433r1091011_rule","rule_id":"SV-271433","rule_version":"OL09-00-000003","rule_title":"OL 9 must be configured so that a separate file system must be used for user home directories (such as /home or an equivalent).","fix_text":"Migrate the \"/home\" directory onto a separate file system/partition.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 uses a separate file system for user home directories (such as /home or an equivalent) with the following command:\n\n$ mount | grep /home\nUUID=fba5000f-2ffa-4417-90eb-8c54ae74a32f on /home type ext4 (rw,nodev,nosuid,noexec,seclabel)\n\nIf a separate entry for \"/home\" is not in use, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Ensuring that \"/home\" is mounted on its own partition enables the setting of more restrictive mount options, and also helps ensure that users cannot trivially fill partitions used for log or audit data storage.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"1991","uuid":"90fc4db2-bde3-405c-a14b-43d97f9aaab4","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7D5ECD833111CE81FB0C32B272C31C5D289A5368\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'OL 9 must be configured so that a separate file system must be used for user home directories (such as /home or an equivalent).' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271434","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271434","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271434","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-271434r1091014_rule","rule_id":"SV-271434","rule_version":"OL09-00-000004","rule_title":"OL 9 must use a separate file system for /tmp.","fix_text":"Migrate the \"/tmp\" path onto a separate file system.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 uses a separate file system/partition for \"/tmp\" with the following command:\n\n$ mount | grep /tmp \ntmpfs /tmp tmpfs noatime,mode=1777 0 0\n\nIf a separate entry for \"/tmp\" is not in use, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The \"/tmp\" partition is used as temporary storage by many programs. Placing \"/tmp\" in its own partition enables the setting of more restrictive mount options, which can help protect programs that use it.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"9417","uuid":"58eb7d58-b1ac-44e8-a97a-555b7128b59d","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 3CF435639F21F8CAEEFC9E4E2E83764E93A14395\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'OL 9 must use a separate file system for /tmp.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271435","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271435","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271435","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-271435r1091017_rule","rule_id":"SV-271435","rule_version":"OL09-00-000005","rule_title":"OL 9 must use a separate file system for /var.","fix_text":"Migrate the \"/var\" path onto a separate file system.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 uses a separate file system/partition for \"/var\" with the following command:\n\n$ mount | grep /var\nUUID=c274f65f-c5b5-4481-b007-bee96feb8b05 /var xfs noatime 1 2\n\nIf a separate entry for \"/var\" is not in use, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Ensuring that \"/var\" is mounted on its own partition enables the setting of more restrictive mount options. This helps protect system services such as daemons or other programs which use it. It is not uncommon for the \"/var\" directory to contain world-writable directories installed by other software packages.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5280","uuid":"a0497318-63c9-4720-8608-cd252323a9f7","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 05DDC819D29BE63C3FD44F04D73553E0FB63ADF1\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'OL 9 must use a separate file system for /var.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271436","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271436","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271436","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-271436r1091020_rule","rule_id":"SV-271436","rule_version":"OL09-00-000006","rule_title":"OL 9 must use a separate file system for /var/log.","fix_text":"Migrate the \"/var/log\" path onto a separate file system.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 uses a separate file system/partition for \"/var/log\" with the following command:\n\n$ mount | grep /var/log\nUUID=c274f65f-c5b5-4486-b021-bee96feb8b21 /var/log xfs noatime 1 2\n\nIf a separate entry for \"/var/log\" is not in use, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Placing \"/var/log\" in its own partition enables better separation between log files and other files in \"/var/\".","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"3541","uuid":"6f19edd5-a43c-40b8-9770-14ab0c1f3ec8","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 56012340F8E38573330299AEC13AEE32354B4DE0\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'OL 9 must use a separate file system for /var/log.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271437","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271437","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271437","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-271437r1091023_rule","rule_id":"SV-271437","rule_version":"OL09-00-000007","rule_title":"OL 9 must use a separate file system for /var/tmp.","fix_text":"Migrate the \"/var/tmp\" path onto a separate file system.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 uses a separate file system/partition for \"/var/tmp\" with the following command:\n\n$ mount | grep /var/tmp\nUUID=c274f65f-c5b5-4379-b017-bee96feb7a34 /var/log xfs noatime 1 2\n\nIf a separate entry for \"/var/tmp\" is not in use, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The \"/var/tmp\" partition is used as temporary storage by many programs. Placing \"/var/tmp\" in its own partition enables the setting of more restrictive mount options, which can help protect programs that use it.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4820","uuid":"a753362d-c16e-4039-a68f-8a425d626cfd","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 092B225CBE898BD95735ADEB6D154A8326785641\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'OL 9 must use a separate file system for /var/tmp.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271438","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271438","title":"SRG-OS-000439-GPOS-00195","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271438","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000439-GPOS-00195","rule_id_src":"SV-271438r1155341_rule","rule_id":"SV-271438","rule_version":"OL09-00-000010","rule_title":"OL 9 must be a vendor supported release.","fix_text":"Upgrade OL 9 to a supported version.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify OL 9 is vendor supported with the following command:\n\n$ cat /etc/oracle-release \nOracle Linux Server release 9.6\n\nIf the installed version of OL 9 is not supported, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"An operating system release is considered \"supported\" if the vendor continues to provide security patches for the product. With an unsupported release, it will not be possible to resolve security issues discovered in the system software.\n\nEnd Of Life dates for Oracle Linux 9 releases are as follows:\nCurrent end of Premier Support for Oracle Linux 9 is June 2032.\nCurrent end of Extended Support for Oracle Linux 9 is June 2035. \n\nEach minor version reaches end of life when the new version is released.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002605"],"reference_identifier":"8993","uuid":"35b64ab1-ba78-44db-8035-ebc2cb0756c9","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 79126DAC125944E3663746E62BFF342021E1B672\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'OL 9 must be a vendor supported release.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271439","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271439","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271439","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-271439r1091029_rule","rule_id":"SV-271439","rule_version":"OL09-00-000015","rule_title":"OL 9 vendor packaged system security patches and updates must be installed and up to date.","fix_text":"Install OL 9 security patches and updates at the organizationally defined frequency. If system updates are installed via a centralized repository that is configured on the system, all updates can be installed with the following command:\n\n$ sudo dnf update -y","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 security patches and updates are installed and up to date. Updates are required to be applied with a frequency determined by organizational policy.\n\nObtain the list of available package security updates from Oracle. The URL for updates is https://linux.oracle.com/errata/. It is important to note that updates provided by Oracle may not be present on the system if the underlying packages are not installed.\n\nCheck that the available package security updates have been installed on the system with the following command:\n\n$ dnf history list | more\n\n    ID | Command line | Date and time | Action(s) | Altered    \n-------------------------------------------------------------------------------    \n   70 | install aide | 2023-03-05 10:58 | Install | 1    \n   69 | update -y | 2023-03-04 14:34 | Update | 18 EE    \n   68 | install vlc | 2023-02-21 17:12 | Install | 21   \n   67 | update -y | 2023-02-21 17:04 | Update | 7 EE \n\nTypical update frequency may be overridden by Information Assurance Vulnerability Alert (IAVA) notifications from CYBERCOM.\n\nIf the system is in noncompliance with the organizational patching policy, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Installing software updates is a fundamental mitigation against the exploitation of publicly known vulnerabilities. If the most recent security patches and updates are not installed, unauthorized users may take advantage of weaknesses in the unpatched software. The lack of prompt attention to patching could result in a system compromise.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"7519","uuid":"d9d07659-a552-4050-a77a-1f8811dc212c","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 49BB41898516FE86289B6EBEDFEB519D52B9EDC5\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'OL 9 vendor packaged system security patches and updates must be installed and up to date.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271440","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271440","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271440","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-271440r1092462_rule","rule_id":"SV-271440","rule_version":"OL09-00-000020","rule_title":"OL 9 must be configured so that the graphical display manager is not the default target unless approved.","fix_text":"Configure OL 9 to boot to the command line.\n\nSet the default target to multi-user with the following command:\n$ sudo systemctl set-default multi-user.target\n\nIf there is an operational requirement for a graphical user interface, document it with the ISSO.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 is configured to boot to the command line:\n\n$ systemctl get-default\nmulti-user.target\n\nIf the system default target is not set to \"multi-user.target\" and the information system security officer (ISSO) lacks a documented requirement for a graphical user interface, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unnecessary service packages must not be installed to decrease the attack surface of the system. Graphical display managers have a long history of security vulnerabilities and must not be used unless approved and documented.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"9046","uuid":"d5e5bcc2-8205-4b95-9c84-b3eacbc1b1d1","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: EC80EC2494D71E398D995DE8AB5B1E95DBF85BB6\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'OL 9 must be configured so that the graphical display manager is not the default target unless approved.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271441","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271441","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271441","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-271441r1137691_rule","rule_id":"SV-271441","rule_version":"OL09-00-000025","rule_title":"OL 9 must require authentication to access emergency mode.","fix_text":"Configure OL 9 to require authentication for emergency mode.\n\nAdd or modify the following line in the \"/usr/lib/systemd/system/emergency.service\" file:\n\nExecStart=-/usr/lib/systemd/systemd-sulogin-shell emergency","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 requires authentication for emergency mode with the following command:\n\n$ grep sulogin-shell /usr/lib/systemd/system/emergency.service \nExecStart=-/usr/lib/systemd/systemd-sulogin-shell emergency\n\nIf this line is not returned, or is commented out, this is a finding. If the output is different, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"To mitigate the risk of unauthorized access to sensitive information by entities that have been issued certificates by DOD-approved PKIs, all DOD systems (e.g., web servers and web portals) must be properly configured to incorporate access control methods that do not rely solely on the possession of a certificate for access. Successful authentication must not automatically give an entity access to an asset or security boundary. Authorization procedures and controls must be implemented to ensure each authenticated entity also has a validated and current authorization. Authorization is the process of determining whether an entity, once authenticated, is permitted to access a specific asset. Information systems use access control policies and enforcement mechanisms to implement this requirement.\n\nThis requirement prevents attackers with physical access from trivially bypassing security on the machine and gaining root access. Such accesses are further prevented by configuring the bootloader password.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"9564","uuid":"847ff4de-22a0-4fe3-83ae-872701b07056","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 12D7AF9D43ECF960222641C2470A35835E99C492\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'OL 9 must require authentication to access emergency mode.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271442","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271442","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271442","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-271442r1137691_rule","rule_id":"SV-271442","rule_version":"OL09-00-000030","rule_title":"OL 9 must require authentication to access single-user mode.","fix_text":"Configure OL 9 to require authentication for single-user mode.\n\nAdd or modify the following line in the \"/usr/lib/systemd/system/rescue.service\" file:\n\nExecStart=-/usr/lib/systemd/systemd-sulogin-shell rescue","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 requires authentication for single-user mode with the following command:\n\n$ grep sulogin /usr/lib/systemd/system/rescue.service \nExecStart=-/usr/lib/systemd/systemd-sulogin-shell rescue\n\nIf this line is not returned, or is commented out, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"To mitigate the risk of unauthorized access to sensitive information by entities that have been issued certificates by DOD-approved PKIs, all DOD systems (e.g., web servers and web portals) must be properly configured to incorporate access control methods that do not rely solely on the possession of a certificate for access. Successful authentication must not automatically give an entity access to an asset or security boundary. Authorization procedures and controls must be implemented to ensure each authenticated entity also has a validated and current authorization. Authorization is the process of determining whether an entity, once authenticated, is permitted to access a specific asset. Information systems use access control policies and enforcement mechanisms to implement this requirement.\n\nThis requirement prevents attackers with physical access from trivially bypassing security on the machine and gaining root access. Such accesses are further prevented by configuring the bootloader password.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"4428","uuid":"b8f561f6-e620-4ec2-a6cb-6e560bf6bb13","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 28312C0E83E96B3747D5A749F790EAF3AD57A3F7\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'OL 9 must require authentication to access single-user mode.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271443","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271443","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271443","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-271443r1092463_rule","rule_id":"SV-271443","rule_version":"OL09-00-000040","rule_title":"OL 9 must be configured to disable the Asynchronous Transfer Mode (ATM) kernel module.","fix_text":"Configure OL 9 to prevent the atm kernel module from being loaded.\n\nAdd the following line to the file /etc/modprobe.d/atm.conf (or create atm.conf if it does not exist):\n\ninstall atm /bin/false\nblacklist atm","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 disables the ability to load the ATM kernel module with the following command:\n\n$ grep -r atm /etc/modprobe.conf /etc/modprobe.d/* \ninstall atm /bin/false\nblacklist atm\n\nIf the command does not return any output, or the line is commented out, and use of ATM is not documented with the information system security officer (ISSO) as an operational requirement, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Disabling ATM protects the system against exploitation of any flaws in its implementation.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5543","uuid":"0d0a29f0-b6d5-4217-a7b1-f5c036eea5cc","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E9791884A1E8A3E58D3F747A76BCCAFF2B1350F3\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'OL 9 must be configured to disable the Asynchronous Transfer Mode (ATM) kernel module.' is not present or not in use on this the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271444","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271444","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271444","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-271444r1091044_rule","rule_id":"SV-271444","rule_version":"OL09-00-000041","rule_title":"OL 9 must be configured to disable the Controller Area Network (CAN) kernel module.","fix_text":"Configure OL 9 to prevent the can kernel module from being loaded.\n\nAdd the following line to the file /etc/modprobe.d/can.conf (or create atm.conf if it does not exist):\n\ninstall can /bin/false\nblacklist can","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 disables the ability to load the CAN kernel module with the following command:\n\n$ grep -r can /etc/modprobe.conf /etc/modprobe.d/* \ninstall can /bin/false\nblacklist can\n\nIf the command does not return any output, or the line is commented out, and use of CAN is not documented with the information system security officer (ISSO) as an operational requirement, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Disabling CAN protects the system against exploitation of any flaws in its implementation.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4121","uuid":"3ebcf3ca-565d-4034-8bc0-af761c2010d8","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 60A5F7CB0AC354B12D6A522E338FABC9648918F0\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'OL 9 must be configured to disable the Controller Area Network (CAN) kernel module.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271445","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271445","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271445","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-271445r1091047_rule","rule_id":"SV-271445","rule_version":"OL09-00-000042","rule_title":"OL 9 must be configured to disable the FireWire kernel module.","fix_text":"Configure OL 9 to prevent the firewire-core kernel module from being loaded.\n\nAdd the following line to the file /etc/modprobe.d/firewire-core.conf (or create firewire-core.conf if it does not exist):\n\ninstall firewire-core /bin/true\nblacklist firewire-core","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 disables the ability to load the firewire-core kernel module with the following command:\n\n$ grep -r firewire-core /etc/modprobe.conf /etc/modprobe.d/* \ninstall firewire-core /bin/true\nblacklist firewire-core\n\nIf the command does not return any output, or the line is commented out, and use of firewire-core is not documented with the information system security officer (ISSO) as an operational requirement, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Disabling firewire protects the system against exploitation of any flaws in its implementation.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"8534","uuid":"1d8bbb38-b123-4f6b-86c8-65544dd7b2ea","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8358C073D7E4D085161F639830B8F8AB58D3845D\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'OL 9 must be configured to disable the FireWire kernel module.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271446","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271446","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271446","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-271446r1155293_rule","rule_id":"SV-271446","rule_version":"OL09-00-000043","rule_title":"OL 9 must disable the Stream Control Transmission Protocol (SCTP) kernel module.","fix_text":"Configure OL 9 to prevent the sctp kernel module from being loaded.\n\nAdd the following line to the file /etc/modprobe.d/sctp.conf (or create sctp.conf if it does not exist):\n\ninstall sctp /bin/false\nblacklist sctp","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify OL 9 disables the ability to load the sctp kernel module with the following command:\n\n$ grep -irs sctp /etc/modprobe.conf /etc/modprobe.d/*\n/etc/modprobe.d/sctp.conf:install sctp /bin/false\n/etc/modprobe.d/sctp.conf:blacklist sctp\n\nIf the command does not return any output, or the line is commented out, and use of sctp is not documented with the information system security officer (ISSO) as an operational requirement, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"It is detrimental for operating systems to provide, or install by default, functionality exceeding requirements or mission objectives. These unnecessary capabilities or services are often overlooked and therefore may remain unsecured. They increase the risk to the platform by providing additional attack vectors.\n\nFailing to disconnect unused protocols can result in a system compromise.\n\nThe SCTP is a transport layer protocol, designed to support the idea of message-oriented communication, with several streams of messages within one connection. Disabling SCTP protects the system against exploitation of any flaws in its implementation.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"2140","uuid":"4a141043-04a9-425e-9073-aed763b83201","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4C9F88E7D67C5EAB02A93FE73C7E8D7238B8A2F6\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'OL 9 must disable the Stream Control Transmission Protocol (SCTP) kernel module.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271447","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271447","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271447","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-271447r1155295_rule","rule_id":"SV-271447","rule_version":"OL09-00-000044","rule_title":"OL 9 must disable the Transparent Inter Process Communication (TIPC) kernel module.","fix_text":"Configure OL 9 to prevent the tipc kernel module from being loaded.\n\nAdd the following line to the file /etc/modprobe.d/tipc.conf (or create tipc.conf if it does not exist):\n\ninstall tipc /bin/false\nblacklist tipc","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify OL 9 disables the ability to load the tipc kernel module with the following command:\n\n$ grep -irs tipc /etc/modprobe.conf /etc/modprobe.d/*\n/etc/modprobe.d/tipc.conf:install tipc /bin/false\n/etc/modprobe.d/tipc.conf:blacklist tipc\n\nIf the command does not return any output, or the line is commented out, and use of TIPC is not documented with the information system security officer (ISSO) as an operational requirement, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"It is detrimental for operating systems to provide, or install by default, functionality exceeding requirements or mission objectives. These unnecessary capabilities or services are often overlooked and therefore may remain unsecured. They increase the risk to the platform by providing additional attack vectors.\n\nFailing to disconnect unused protocols can result in a system compromise.\n\nThe TIPC is a protocol that is specially designed for intra-cluster communication. It can be configured to transmit messages either on UDP or directly across Ethernet. Message delivery is sequence guaranteed, loss free, and flow controlled. Disabling TIPC protects the system against exploitation of any flaws in its implementation.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"3479","uuid":"1ab3c37a-6096-4e7c-a3c6-ad69efd0bcb1","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D80E2A0667B8C33FCF9668C2845DB496C23E7B06\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'OL 9 must disable the Transparent Inter Process Communication (TIPC) kernel module.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271448","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271448","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271448","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-271448r1155297_rule","rule_id":"SV-271448","rule_version":"OL09-00-000045","rule_title":"OL 9 must disable mounting of cramfs.","fix_text":"Configure OL 9 to prevent the cramfs kernel module from being loaded. \n\nAdd the following line to the file /etc/modprobe.d/cramfs.conf (or create blacklist.conf if it does not exist):\n\ninstall cramfs /bin/false\nblacklist cramfs\n\nReboot the system for the settings to take effect.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify OL 9 disables the ability to load the cramfs kernel module with the following command:\n\n$ grep -irs cramfs /etc/modprobe.conf /etc/modprobe.d/*\n/etc/modprobe.d/blacklist.conf:install cramfs /bin/false\n/etc/modprobe.d/blacklist.conf:blacklist cramfs\n\nIf the command does not return any output, or the line is commented out, and use of the cramfs protocol is not documented with the information system security officer (ISSO) as an operational requirement, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"It is detrimental for operating systems to provide, or install by default, functionality exceeding requirements or mission objectives. These unnecessary capabilities or services are often overlooked and therefore may remain unsecured. They increase the risk to the platform by providing additional attack vectors.\n\nRemoving support for unneeded filesystem types reduces the local attack surface of the server.\n\nCompressed ROM/RAM file system (or cramfs) is a read-only file system designed for simplicity and space-efficiency. It is mainly used in embedded and small-footprint systems.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"8079","uuid":"fb4d7de5-de90-43b3-b70c-b1bacac34411","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D37A50E0F3F3821AB8CF76F28C3E32D49EB82363\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'OL 9 must disable mounting of cramfs.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271449","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271449","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271449","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-271449r1091059_rule","rule_id":"SV-271449","rule_version":"OL09-00-000046","rule_title":"OL 9 Bluetooth must be disabled.","fix_text":"Configure OL 9 to disable the Bluetooth adapter when not in use.\n\nCreate or modify the \"/etc/modprobe.d/bluetooth.conf\" file with the following line:\n\ninstall bluetooth /bin/false\nblacklist bluetooth\n\nReboot the system for the settings to take effect.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 disables the ability to load the Bluetooth kernel module with the following command:\n\n$ grep -r bluetooth /etc/modprobe.conf /etc/modprobe.d/* \ninstall bluetooth /bin/false\nblacklist bluetooth\n\nIf the command does not return any output, or the line is commented out, and use of Bluetooth is not documented with the information system security officer (ISSO) as an operational requirement, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This requirement applies to wireless peripheral technologies (e.g., wireless mice, keyboards, displays, etc.) used with OL 9 systems. Wireless peripherals (e.g., Wi-Fi/Bluetooth/IR keyboards, mice and pointing devices, and near field communications [NFC]) present a unique challenge by creating an open, unsecured port on a computer. Wireless peripherals must meet DOD requirements for wireless data transmission and be approved for use by the authorizing official (AO). Even though some wireless peripherals, such as mice and pointing devices, do not ordinarily carry information that need to be protected, modification of communications with these wireless peripherals may be used to compromise the OL 9 operating system.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049, SRG-OS-000300-GPOS-00118","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381","CCI-001443"],"reference_identifier":"3434","uuid":"19e5a904-569d-4bbb-b6ab-fd78fdc85deb","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 01854DD8D437C27A3C238E7814BD4C3575F6BABC\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'OL 9 Bluetooth must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271450","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271450","title":"SRG-OS-000114-GPOS-00059","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271450","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000114-GPOS-00059","rule_id_src":"SV-271450r1092466_rule","rule_id":"SV-271450","rule_version":"OL09-00-000047","rule_title":"OL 9 must be configured to disable USB mass storage.","fix_text":"Configure OL 9 to prevent the usb-storage kernel module from being loaded.\n\nAdd the following line to the file /etc/modprobe.d/usb-storage.conf (or create usb-storage.conf if it does not exist):\n\ninstall usb-storage /bin/false\nblacklist usb-storage","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 disables the ability to load the USB Storage kernel module with the following command:\n\n$ grep -r usb-storage /etc/modprobe.conf /etc/modprobe.d/* \ninstall usb-storage /bin/false\nblacklist usb-storage\n\nIf the command does not return any output, or the line is commented out, and use of USB Storage is not documented with the information system security officer (ISSO) as an operational requirement, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"USB mass storage permits easy introduction of unknown devices, thereby facilitating malicious activity.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000114-GPOS-00059, SRG-OS-000378-GPOS-00163","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000778","CCI-001958"],"reference_identifier":"4055","uuid":"e30d24f2-42de-4811-a2ec-e64c91255fbc","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-271451","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271451","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271451","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-271451r1137691_rule","rule_id":"SV-271451","rule_version":"OL09-00-000050","rule_title":"OL 9 must require a unique superuser's name upon booting into single-user and maintenance modes.","fix_text":"Configure OL 9 to have a unique username for the grub superuser account.\n\nEdit the \"/etc/grub.d/01_users\" file and add or modify the following lines in the \"### BEGIN /etc/grub.d/01_users ###\" section:\n\nset superusers=\"superusers-account\"\nexport superusers\n\nOnce the superuser account has been added, update the grub.cfg file by running:\n\n$ sudo grubby --update-kernel=ALL'","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 requires a unique username for the grub superuser account.\n\nVerify the boot loader superuser account has been set with the following command:\n\n$ sudo grep -A1 \"superusers\" /etc/grub2.cfg \n    set superusers=\"<superusers-account>\"\n    export superusers\n    password_pbkdf2 root ${GRUB2_PASSWORD}\n \nThe <superusers-account> is the actual account name different from common names like root, admin, or administrator.\n\nIf superusers contains easily guessable usernames, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Having a nondefault grub superuser username makes password-guessing attacks less effective.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"9146","uuid":"91cab330-f6ae-4fe3-b56a-7a119c5689e9","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D9277AC8BFDE6BA0BAC7544F4B40C19261FE538D\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'OL 9 must require a unique superuser's name upon booting into single-user and maintenance modes.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271452","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271452","title":"SRG-OS-000445-GPOS-00199","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271452","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000445-GPOS-00199","rule_id_src":"SV-271452r1091068_rule","rule_id":"SV-271452","rule_version":"OL09-00-000060","rule_title":"OL 9 must use a Linux Security Module configured to enforce limits on system services.","fix_text":"Configure OL 9 to verify correct operation of security functions.\n\nEdit the file \"/etc/selinux/config\" and add or modify the following line:\n\n SELINUX=enforcing \n\nA reboot is required for the changes to take effect.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 enforces the correct operation of security functions through the use of SELinux with the following command:\n\n$ getenforce\nEnforcing\n\nIf SELINUX is not set to \"Enforcing\", this is a finding.\n\nVerify that SELinux is configured to be enforcing at boot.\n\n$ grep \"SELINUX=\" /etc/selinux/config\n# SELINUX= can take one of these three values:\n# NOTE: In earlier Fedora kernel builds, SELINUX=disabled would also\nSELINUX=enforcing\n\nIf SELINUX line is missing, commented out, or not set to \"enforcing\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Without verification of the security functions, security functions may not operate correctly and the failure may go unnoticed. Security function is defined as the hardware, software, and/or firmware of the information system responsible for enforcing the system security policy and supporting the isolation of code and data on which the protection is based. Security functionality includes, but is not limited to, establishing system accounts, configuring access authorizations (i.e., permissions, privileges), setting events to be audited, and setting intrusion detection parameters.\n\nThis requirement applies to operating systems performing security function verification/testing and/or systems and environments that require this functionality.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000445-GPOS-00199, SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002696","CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"8488","uuid":"4ff69c99-0926-4ec8-b5b1-a0bf498125b6","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-271453","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271453","title":"SRG-OS-000445-GPOS-00199","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271453","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000445-GPOS-00199","rule_id_src":"SV-271453r1091071_rule","rule_id":"SV-271453","rule_version":"OL09-00-000065","rule_title":"OL 9 must enable the SELinux targeted policy.","fix_text":"Configure OL 9 to use the targetd SELINUX policy.\n\nEdit the file \"/etc/selinux/config\" and add or modify the following line:\n\n SELINUXTYPE=targeted \n\nA reboot is required for the changes to take effect.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 enables the SELinux targeted policy with the following command:\n\n$ sestatus | grep policy\nLoaded policy name:             targeted\n\nIf the loaded policy name is not \"targeted\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Setting the SELinux policy to \"targeted\" or a more specialized policy ensures the system will confine processes that are likely to be targeted for exploitation, such as network or system services.\n\nNote: During the development or debugging of SELinux modules, it is common to temporarily place nonproduction systems in \"permissive\" mode. In such temporary cases, SELinux policies should be developed, and once work is completed, the system should be reconfigured to \"targeted\".","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002696"],"reference_identifier":"2548","uuid":"503d87a4-cafb-4374-a5fd-4f0c13335f81","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 66452C6A7168AC4FEAE30C02634A94AE114666C8\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'OL 9 must enable the SELinux targeted policy.' is not present or not in use on this the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271454","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271454","title":"SRG-OS-000033-GPOS-00014","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271454","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000033-GPOS-00014","rule_id_src":"SV-271454r1092458_rule","rule_id":"SV-271454","rule_version":"OL09-00-000070","rule_title":"OL 9 must enable FIPS mode.","fix_text":"Configure OL 9 to implement FIPS mode with the following command:\n\n$ sudo fips-mode-setup --enable\n\nReboot the system for the changes to take effect.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 is in FIPS mode with the following command:\n\n$ fips-mode-setup --check\nFIPS mode is enabled.\n\nIf FIPS mode is not enabled, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Use of weak or untested encryption algorithms undermines the purposes of using encryption to protect data. The operating system must implement cryptographic modules adhering to the higher standards approved by the federal government since this provides assurance they have been tested and validated. This includes NIST FIPS-validated cryptography for the following: Provisioning digital signatures, generating cryptographic hashes, and to protect data requiring data-at-rest protections in accordance with applicable federal laws, Executive Orders, directives, policies, regulations, and standards.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000033-GPOS-00014, SRG-OS-000125-GPOS-00065, SRG-OS-000396-GPOS-00176, SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187, SRG-OS-000478-GPOS-00223","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000068","CCI-000877","CCI-002450","CCI-002418"],"reference_identifier":"9013","uuid":"edf4fdab-d121-4d47-a314-3ff97f4e3bf0","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 541517AE639EB1DA9468AA5DEDE11F6C839F4AAC\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'OL 9 must enable FIPS mode.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271455","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271455","title":"SRG-OS-000023-GPOS-00006","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271455","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000023-GPOS-00006","rule_id_src":"SV-271455r1091077_rule","rule_id":"SV-271455","rule_version":"OL09-00-000090","rule_title":"OL 9 must display the Standard Mandatory DOD Notice and Consent Banner before granting local or remote access to the system via a command line user logon.","fix_text":"Configure OL 9 to display the Standard Mandatory DOD Notice and Consent Banner before granting access to the system via command line logon.\n\nEdit the \"/etc/issue\" file to replace the default text with the Standard Mandatory DOD Notice and Consent Banner. The DOD-required text is:\n\n\"You are accessing a U.S. Government (USG) Information System (IS) that is provided for USG-authorized use only.\n\nBy using this IS (which includes any device attached to this IS), you consent to the following conditions:\n\n-The USG routinely intercepts and monitors communications on this IS for purposes including, but not limited to, penetration testing, COMSEC monitoring, network operations and defense, personnel misconduct (PM), law enforcement (LE), and counterintelligence (CI) investigations.\n\n-At any time, the USG may inspect and seize data stored on this IS.\n\n-Communications using, or data stored on, this IS are not private, are subject to routine monitoring, interception, and search, and may be disclosed or used for any USG-authorized purpose.\n\n-This IS includes security measures (e.g., authentication and access controls) to protect USG interests -- not for your personal benefit or privacy.\n\n-Notwithstanding the above, using this IS does not constitute consent to PM, LE or CI investigative searching or monitoring of the content of privileged communications, or work product, related to personal representation or services by attorneys, psychotherapists, or clergy, and their assistants. Such communications and work product are private and confidential. See User Agreement for details.\"","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 displays the Standard Mandatory DOD Notice and Consent Banner before granting access to the operating system via a command line user logon.\n\nCheck that a banner is displayed at the command line login screen with the following command:\n\n$ cat /etc/issue\n\nIf the banner is set correctly it will return the following text:\n\n\"You are accessing a U.S. Government (USG) Information System (IS) that is provided for USG-authorized use only.\n\nBy using this IS (which includes any device attached to this IS), you consent to the following conditions:\n\n-The USG routinely intercepts and monitors communications on this IS for purposes including, but not limited to, penetration testing, COMSEC monitoring, network operations and defense, personnel misconduct (PM), law enforcement (LE), and counterintelligence (CI) investigations.\n\n-At any time, the USG may inspect and seize data stored on this IS.\n\n-Communications using, or data stored on, this IS are not private, are subject to routine monitoring, interception, and search, and may be disclosed or used for any USG-authorized purpose.\n\n-This IS includes security measures (e.g., authentication and access controls) to protect USG interests--not for your personal benefit or privacy.\n\n-Notwithstanding the above, using this IS does not constitute consent to PM, LE or CI investigative searching or monitoring of the content of privileged communications, or work product, related to personal representation or services by attorneys, psychotherapists, or clergy, and their assistants. Such communications and work product are private and confidential. See User Agreement for details.\"\n\nIf the banner text does not match the Standard Mandatory DOD Notice and Consent Banner exactly, or the line is commented out, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Display of a standardized and approved use notification before granting access to the operating system ensures privacy and security notification verbiage used is consistent with applicable federal laws, Executive Orders, directives, policies, regulations, standards, and guidance.\n\nSystem use notifications are required only for access via login interfaces with human users and are not required when such human interfaces do not exist.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000023-GPOS-00006, SRG-OS-000228-GPOS-00088","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000048","CCI-001384","CCI-001385","CCI-001386","CCI-001387","CCI-001388"],"reference_identifier":"1898","uuid":"c8c3b9f8-f3a7-4a62-8bdf-2a7bb641c525","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 934B2EAFB5FF99B3E9C421D55CB2FF4F348EE74D\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'OL 9 must display the Standard Mandatory DOD Notice and Consent Banner before granting local or remote access to the system via a command line user logon.' is not present or not in use on this the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271456","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271456","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271456","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-271456r1091080_rule","rule_id":"SV-271456","rule_version":"OL09-00-000100","rule_title":"OL 9 must not have the nfs-utils package installed.","fix_text":"Remove the nfs-utils package with the following command:\n\n$ sudo dnf remove nfs-utils","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 does not have the nfs-utils package installed with the following command:\n\n$ dnf list --installed nfs-utils\nError: No matching Packages to list\n\nIf the \"nfs-utils\" package is installed, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"\"nfs-utils\" provides a daemon for the kernel NFS server and related tools. This package also contains the \"showmount\" program. \"showmount\" queries the mount daemon on a remote host for information about the Network File System (NFS) server on the remote host. For example, \"showmount\" can display the clients that are mounted on that host.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"9489","uuid":"e8f5bc93-0d36-4fa8-8346-96d3288d8f7f","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 947F0EDC7087397AA34A2BF0591E34D9BB7B7105\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'OL 9 must not have the nfs-utils package installed.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271457","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271457","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271457","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-271457r1134853_rule","rule_id":"SV-271457","rule_version":"OL09-00-000105","rule_title":"OL 9 must not install packages from the Extra Packages for Enterprise Linux (EPEL) repository.","fix_text":"The repo package can be manually removed with the following command:\n\n$ sudo dnf remove epel-release\n\nConfigure the operating system to disable use of the EPEL repository with the following command:\n\n$ sudo dnf config-manager --set-disabled epel","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 is not able to install packages from the EPEL with the following command:\n\n$ dnf repolist\nrepo id                                               repo name\nol9_UEKR7                                             Oracle Linux 9 UEK Release 7 (x86_64)\nol9_appstream                                         Oracle Linux 9 Application Stream Packages (x86_64)\nol9_baseos_latest                                     Oracle Linux 9 BaseOS Latest (x86_64)\nol9_oraclelinuxmanager210_client                      Oracle Linux Manager Client 2.10 for Oracle Linux 9 (x86_64)\n\nIf any repositories containing the word \"epel\" in the name exist, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The EPEL is a repository of high-quality open-source packages for enterprise-class Linux distributions such as RHEL, CentOS, AlmaLinux, Rocky Linux, and Oracle Linux. These packages are not part of the official distribution but are built using the same Fedora build system to ensure compatibility and maintain quality standards.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"1791","uuid":"d8a92f0f-4a29-4285-8e56-67016bc04706","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-271458","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271458","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271458","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-271458r1091086_rule","rule_id":"SV-271458","rule_version":"OL09-00-000110","rule_title":"OL 9 must not have the telnet-server package installed.","fix_text":"Remove the telnet-server package with the following command:\n\n$ sudo dnf remove telnet-server","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 does not have the telnet-server package installed with the following command:\n\n$ dnf list --installed telnet-server\nError: No matching Packages to list\n\nIf the \"telnet-server\" package is installed, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"It is detrimental for operating systems to provide, or install by default, functionality exceeding requirements or mission objectives. These unnecessary capabilities are often overlooked and therefore, may remain unsecure. They increase the risk to the platform by providing additional attack vectors.\n\nThe telnet service provides an unencrypted remote access service, which does not provide for the confidentiality and integrity of user passwords or the remote session. If a privileged user were to login using this service, the privileged user password could be compromised.\n\nRemoving the \"telnet-server\" package decreases the risk of accidental (or intentional) activation of the telnet service.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"8203","uuid":"6c8439f9-d042-4d48-84f2-a1bda8cadc25","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2827FD2A5597E42E6DE2E0958FFFD934E29A0C9C\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'OL 9 must not have the telnet-server package installed.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271459","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271459","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271459","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-271459r1184166_rule","rule_id":"SV-271459","rule_version":"OL09-00-000115","rule_title":"OL 9 must not have the gssproxy package installed.","fix_text":"Remove the gssproxy package with the following command:\n\n$ sudo dnf remove gssproxy","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Note: If NFS mounts are authorized and in use on the system, this is not applicable.\n\nVerify OL 9 does not have the gssproxy package installed with the following command:\n\n$ dnf list --installed gssproxy\nError: No matching Packages to list\n\nIf the \"gssproxy\" package is installed and is not documented with the information system security officer (ISSO) as an operational requirement, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"It is detrimental for operating systems to provide, or install by default, functionality exceeding requirements or mission objectives. These unnecessary capabilities or services are often overlooked and therefore, may remain unsecured. They increase the risk to the platform by providing additional attack vectors.\n\nOperating systems are capable of providing a wide variety of functions and services. Some of the functions and services provided by default may not be necessary to support essential organizational operations (e.g., key missions, functions).\n\nThe gssproxy package is a proxy for GSS API credential handling and could expose secrets on some networks. It is not needed for normal function of the OS.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5831","uuid":"ff62ab55-4072-4984-8380-f8ff61a44940","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 6F6DC1DA341A504E7E92DF03A4936DA101F9C81C\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'OL 9 must not have the gssproxy package installed.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271460","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271460","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271460","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-271460r1091092_rule","rule_id":"SV-271460","rule_version":"OL09-00-000120","rule_title":"OL 9 must not have the iprutils package installed.","fix_text":"Remove the iprutils package with the following command:\n\n$ sudo dnf remove iprutils","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 does not have the iprutils package installed with the following command:\n\n$ dnf list --installed iprutils\nError: No matching Packages to list\n\nIf the \"iprutils\" package is installed and is not documented with the information system security officer (ISSO) as an operational requirement, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"It is detrimental for operating systems to provide, or install by default, functionality exceeding requirements or mission objectives. These unnecessary capabilities or services are often overlooked and therefore may remain unsecured. They increase the risk to the platform by providing additional attack vectors.\n\nOperating systems are capable of providing a wide variety of functions and services. Some of the functions and services, provided by default, may not be necessary to support essential organizational operations (e.g., key missions, functions).\n\nThe iprutils package provides a suite of utilities to manage and configure SCSI devices supported by the ipr SCSI storage device driver.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"2954","uuid":"64bfe621-ddcb-4c83-83ec-73f2291b03ce","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-271461","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271461","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271461","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-271461r1091095_rule","rule_id":"SV-271461","rule_version":"OL09-00-000125","rule_title":"OL 9 must not have the tuned package installed.","fix_text":"Remove the tuned package with the following command:\n\n$ sudo dnf remove tuned","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 does not have the tuned package installed with the following command:\n\n$ dnf list --installed tuned\nError: No matching Packages to list\n\nIf the \"tuned\" package is installed and is not documented with the information system security officer (ISSO) as an operational requirement, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"It is detrimental for operating systems to provide, or install by default, functionality exceeding requirements or mission objectives. These unnecessary capabilities or services are often overlooked and therefore may remain unsecured. They increase the risk to the platform by providing additional attack vectors.\n\nOperating systems are capable of providing a wide variety of functions and services. Some of the functions and services, provided by default, may not be necessary to support essential organizational operations (e.g., key missions, functions).\n\nThe tuned package contains a daemon that tunes the system settings dynamically. It does so by monitoring the usage of several system components periodically. Based on that information, components will then be put into lower or higher power savings modes to adapt to the current usage. The tuned package is not needed for normal OS operations.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"8808","uuid":"723bd497-bf38-4bbb-a2cc-a9a736f3a17f","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 6A190BDA14422FDA4BA7A8FE9507A7C663932114\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'OL 9 must not have the tuned package installed.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271462","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271462","title":"SRG-OS-000074-GPOS-00042","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271462","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000074-GPOS-00042","rule_id_src":"SV-271462r1184169_rule","rule_id":"SV-271462","rule_version":"OL09-00-000130","rule_title":"OL 9 must not have a File Transfer Protocol (FTP) server package installed.","fix_text":"Remove the vsftpd package with the following command:\n\n$ sudo dnf remove vsftpd","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify OL 9 does not have an FTP server package installed with the following command:\n\n$ dnf list --installed | grep vsftpd\n\nIf the \"vsftpd\" package is installed, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The FTP service provides an unencrypted remote access that does not provide for the confidentiality and integrity of user passwords or the remote session. If a privileged user were to log on using this service, the privileged user password could be compromised. SSH or other encrypted file transfer methods must be used in place of this service.\n\nRemoving the \"vsftpd\" package decreases the risk of accidental activation.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000074-GPOS-00042, SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000197","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"3101","uuid":"1e09d71e-5d6e-478b-b145-a55c11ee24ab","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C711257AF265A58DBCAF79B0AC3AD18658EF53B6\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'OL 9 must not have a File Transfer Protocol (FTP) server package installed.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271463","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271463","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271463","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-271463r1184172_rule","rule_id":"SV-271463","rule_version":"OL09-00-000135","rule_title":"OL 9 must not have a Trivial File Transfer Protocol (TFTP) server package installed.","fix_text":"Remove the tftp-server package with the following command:\n\n$ sudo dnf remove tftp-server","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify OL 9 does not have a tftp server package installed with the following command:\n\n$ dnf list --installed | grep tftp-server\n\nIf the \"tftp-server\" package is installed, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Removing the \"tftp-server\" package decreases the risk of the accidental (or intentional) activation of tftp services.\n\nIf TFTP is required for operational support (such as transmission of router configurations), its use must be documented with the information systems security manager (ISSM), restricted to only authorized personnel, and have access control rules established.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5162","uuid":"26f8f3a4-ace2-41a0-98d9-97412ea3b324","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 74024249863547B40809D9A1946E0764D5069422\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'OL 9 must not have a Trivial File Transfer Protocol (TFTP) server package installed.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271465","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271465","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271465","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-271465r1091107_rule","rule_id":"SV-271465","rule_version":"OL09-00-000145","rule_title":"OL 9 must not have a graphical display manager installed unless approved.","fix_text":"Remove all xorg packages with the following command:\n\nWarning: If accessing the system through the graphical user interface, change to the multi-user.target with the following command:\n\n$ sudo systemctl isolate multi-user.target\n\nWarning: Removal of the graphical user interface will immediately render it useless. The following commands must not be run from a virtual terminal emulator in the graphical interface.\n\n$ sudo dnf remove \"xorg*\"\n$ sudo systemctl set-default multi-user.target\n\nIf there is an operational requirement for a graphical user interface it must be documented with the ISSO.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 does not have a graphical user interface installed with the following command:\n\n$ dnf list --installed \"xorg*common\"\nError: No matching Packages to list\n\nIf the \"x11-server-common\" package is installed, and the use of a graphical user interface has not been documented with the information system security officer (ISSO) as an operational requirement, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unnecessary service packages must not be installed to decrease the attack surface of the system. Graphical display managers have a long history of security vulnerabilities and must not be used, unless approved and documented.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000382"],"reference_identifier":"8230","uuid":"a84fbb1b-1d20-4a34-b01c-c7b2450d9ca8","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-271466","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271466","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271466","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-271466r1091110_rule","rule_id":"SV-271466","rule_version":"OL09-00-000150","rule_title":"OL 9 must not have the sendmail package installed.","fix_text":"Remove the sendmail package with the following command:\n\n$ sudo dnf remove sendmail","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 does not have the sendmail package installed with the following command:\n\n$ dnf list --installed sendmail\nError: No matching Packages to list\n\nIf the \"sendmail\" package is installed, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The sendmail software was not developed with security in mind, and its design prevents it from being effectively contained by SELinux. Postfix must be used instead.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"3879","uuid":"4b2a6d14-0035-4001-afbd-e648097cfca6","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 90AF7BAF524B50E6DB6022FDD3933F4AB2CEB258\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'OL 9 must not have the sendmail package installed.' is not present or not in use on this the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271467","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271467","title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271467","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","rule_id_src":"SV-271467r1091113_rule","rule_id":"SV-271467","rule_version":"OL09-00-000200","rule_title":"OL 9 must have policycoreutils package installed.","fix_text":"Install the policycoreutils package with the following command:\n \n$ sudo dnf install -y policycoreutils","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 has the policycoreutils package installed with the following command:\n\n$ dnf list --installed policycoreutils\nInstalled Packages\npolicycoreutils.x86_64                                       3.6-2.1.el9                                       @anaconda                                               \n\nIf the \"policycoreutils\" package is not installed, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Without verification of the security functions, security functions may not operate correctly and the failure may go unnoticed. Security function is defined as the hardware, software, and/or firmware of the information system responsible for enforcing the system security policy and supporting the isolation of code and data on which the protection is based. Security functionality includes, but is not limited to, establishing system accounts, configuring access authorizations (i.e., permissions, privileges), setting events to be audited, and setting intrusion detection parameters.\n\nPolicycoreutils contains the policy core utilities that are required for basic operation of an SELinux-enabled system. These utilities include load_policy to load SELinux policies, setfile to label filesystems, newrole to switch roles, and run_init to run /etc/init.d scripts in the proper context.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"1974","uuid":"b6cbf6b7-e063-4fd1-bf2a-078cf5462312","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1BB5E9144E1C1771E73655CB8210088FC1481FFB\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'OL 9 must have policycoreutils package installed.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271468","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271468","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271468","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-271468r1091116_rule","rule_id":"SV-271468","rule_version":"OL09-00-000210","rule_title":"OL 9 policycoreutils-python-utils package must be installed.","fix_text":"Install the policycoreutils-python-utils service package (if the policycoreutils-python-utils service is not already installed) with the following command:\n\n$ sudo dnf install -y policycoreutils-python-utils","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 policycoreutils-python-utils service package is installed with the following command:\n\n$ dnf list --installed policycoreutils-python-utils\nInstalled Packages\npolicycoreutils-python-utils.noarch                                3.6-2.1.el9                                @AppStream\n\nIf the \"policycoreutils-python-utils\" package is not installed, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The policycoreutils-python-utils package is required to operate and manage an SELinux environment and its policies. It provides utilities such as semanage, audit2allow, audit2why, chcat, and sandbox.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"3109","uuid":"7a04fdd6-8d40-4bc0-b012-6384c1dbb8e4","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: DEE14A6C04EB02712092066BB143676D76A93C42\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'OL 9 policycoreutils-python-utils package must be installed.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271469","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271469","title":"SRG-OS-000096-GPOS-00050","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271469","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000096-GPOS-00050","rule_id_src":"SV-271469r1091119_rule","rule_id":"SV-271469","rule_version":"OL09-00-000220","rule_title":"OL 9 must have the firewalld package installed.","fix_text":"Install the firewalld package with the following command:\n\n$ sudo dnf install -y firewalld","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 has the firewalld package installed with the following command:\n\n$ dnf list --installed firewalld \nInstalled Packages\nfirewalld.noarch                                        1.3.4-1.0.1.el9                                        @anaconda\n\nIf the \"firewall\" package is not installed, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Firewalld provides an easy and effective way to block/limit remote access to the system via ports, services, and protocols.\n\nRemote access services, such as those providing remote access to network devices and information systems, which lack automated control capabilities, increase risk and make remote user access management difficult at best.\n\nRemote access is access to DOD nonpublic information systems by an authorized user (or an information system) communicating through an external, nonorganization-controlled network. Remote access methods include, for example, dial-up, broadband, and wireless.\n\nOL 9 functionality (e.g., SSH) must be capable of taking enforcement action if the audit reveals unauthorized activity. Automated control of remote access sessions allows organizations to ensure ongoing compliance with remote access policies by enforcing connection rules of remote access applications on a variety of information system components (e.g., servers, workstations, notebook computers, smartphones, and tablets).\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000096-GPOS-00050, SRG-OS-000297-GPOS-00115, SRG-OS-000298-GPOS-00116, SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00232","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000382","CCI-002314","CCI-002322"],"reference_identifier":"9533","uuid":"a5fbe363-d50f-40c3-8d7c-47b168f87a3c","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 39E5591DCB23B2D329CDC46C7B828569B1A645EC\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'OL 9 must have the firewalld package installed.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271470","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271470","title":"SRG-OS-000096-GPOS-00050","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271470","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000096-GPOS-00050","rule_id_src":"SV-271470r1092618_rule","rule_id":"SV-271470","rule_version":"OL09-00-000221","rule_title":"OL 9 must be configured so that the firewalld service is active.","fix_text":"Enable the firewalld service with the following command:\n\n$ sudo systemctl enable --now firewalld\n\nNote: If firewalld is masked, run following command:\n\nsudo systemctl unmask firewalld","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 firewalld is active with the following command:\n\n$ systemctl is-active firewalld \nactive\n\nIf the firewalld service is not active, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Firewalld provides an easy and effective way to block/limit remote access to the system via ports, services, and protocols.\n\nRemote access services, such as those providing remote access to network devices and information systems, which lack automated control capabilities, increase risk and make remote user access management difficult at best.\n\nRemote access is access to DOD nonpublic information systems by an authorized user (or an information system) communicating through an external, nonorganization-controlled network. Remote access methods include, for example, dial-up, broadband, and wireless.\n\nOL 9 functionality (e.g., RDP) must be capable of taking enforcement action if the audit reveals unauthorized activity. Automated control of remote access sessions allows organizations to ensure ongoing compliance with remote access policies by enforcing connection rules of remote access applications on a variety of information system components (e.g., servers, workstations, notebook computers, smartphones, and tablets).\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000096-GPOS-00050, SRG-OS-000297-GPOS-00115","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000382","CCI-002314"],"reference_identifier":"6579","uuid":"67cf6f37-fe07-43ea-99ce-e9c3ceb06ca4","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 983ED7BFE8E526447CC0B6608D47CEC010E81409\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'OL 9 must be configured so that the firewalld service is active.' is not present or not in use on this the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271471","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271471","title":"SRG-OS-000096-GPOS-00050","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271471","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000096-GPOS-00050","rule_id_src":"SV-271471r1091125_rule","rule_id":"SV-271471","rule_version":"OL09-00-000222","rule_title":"OL 9 must be configured to prohibit or restrict the use of functions, ports, protocols, and/or services, as defined in the Ports, Protocols, and Services Management (PPSM) Category Assignments List (CAL) and vulnerability assessments.","fix_text":"Update the firewall settings and/or running services to comply with the PPSM CLSA for the site or program and the PPSM CAL.\n\nThen run the following command to load the newly created rule(s):\n\n$ sudo firewall-cmd --reload","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify OL 9 is configured to prohibit or restrict the use of functions, ports, protocols, and/or services that are unnecessary or prohibited. \n\nInspect the firewall configuration and running services to verify which services are currently active with the following command:\n\n$ sudo firewall-cmd --list-all-zones\ncustom (active)\ntarget: DROP\nicmp-block-inversion: no\ninterfaces: ens33\nsources: \nservices: dhcpv6-client dns http https ldaps rpc-bind ssh\nports: \nmasquerade: no\nforward-ports: \nicmp-blocks: \nrich rules: \n\nAsk the system administrator for the site or program PPSM Component Local Service Assessment (CLSA). Verify the services allowed by the firewall match the PPSM CLSA. \n\nIf there are additional ports, protocols, or services that are not in the PPSM CLSA, or there are ports, protocols, or services that are prohibited by the PPSM CAL, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"To prevent unauthorized connection of devices, unauthorized transfer of information, or unauthorized tunneling (i.e., embedding of data types within data types), organizations must disable or restrict unused or unnecessary ports, protocols, and services on information systems.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000382"],"reference_identifier":"7339","uuid":"1f1401f5-184e-4999-aeec-f7c15e48a6d8","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D1280FFACB45DCBC5DFD0112C831AA6C3E9B71DD\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'OL 9 must be configured to prohibit or restrict the use of functions, ports, protocols, and/or services, as defined in the Ports, Protocols, and Services Management (PPSM) Category Assignments List (CAL) and vulnerability assessments.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271472","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271472","title":"SRG-OS-000096-GPOS-00050","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271472","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000096-GPOS-00050","rule_id_src":"SV-271472r1091128_rule","rule_id":"SV-271472","rule_version":"OL09-00-000223","rule_title":"OL 9 must control remote access methods.","fix_text":"Configure OL 9 to allow approved settings and/or running services to comply with the PPSM CLSA for the site or program and the PPSM CAL.\n\nTo open a port for a service, configure firewalld using the following command:\n\n$ sudo firewall-cmd --permanent --add-port=port_number/tcp\nor\n$ sudo firewall-cmd --permanent --add-service=service_name","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 controls remote access methods.\n\nInspect the list of enabled firewall ports and verify they are configured correctly by running the following command:\n\n$ sudo firewall-cmd --list-all \n\nAsk the system administrator for the site or program Ports, Protocols, and Services Management Component Local Service Assessment (PPSM CLSA). Verify the services allowed by the firewall match the PPSM CLSA. \n\nIf there are additional ports, protocols, or services that are not in the PPSM CLSA, or there are ports, protocols, or services that are prohibited by the PPSM Category Assurance List (CAL), or there are no firewall rules configured, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"To prevent unauthorized connection of devices, unauthorized transfer of information, or unauthorized tunneling (i.e., embedding of data types within data types), organizations must disable or restrict unused or unnecessary physical and logical ports/protocols on information systems.\n\nOperating systems are capable of providing a wide variety of functions and services. Some of the functions and services provided by default may not be necessary to support essential organizational operations. Additionally, it is sometimes convenient to provide multiple services from a single component (e.g., VPN and IPS); however, doing so increases risk over limiting the services provided by one component.\n\nTo support the requirements and principles of least functionality, the operating system must support the organizational requirements, providing only essential capabilities and limiting the use of ports, protocols, and/or services to only those required, authorized, and approved to conduct official business.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000096-GPOS-00050, SRG-OS-000297-GPOS-00115","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000382","CCI-002314"],"reference_identifier":"6782","uuid":"c2134c1e-cdfa-427c-9b0c-6f6ab7dc8403","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9129F8570BCD0ADDE72B8791A4FC4A6DDDEDF399\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'OL 9 must control remote access methods.' is not present or not in use on this the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271473","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271473","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271473","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-271473r1091131_rule","rule_id":"SV-271473","rule_version":"OL09-00-000224","rule_title":"OL 9 must be configured so that the firewall employs a deny-all, allow-by-exception policy for allowing connections to other systems.","fix_text":"Configure the firewalld daemon to employ a deny-all, allow-by-exception with the following commands:\n\nStart by adding the exceptions that are required for mission functionality to the \"drop\" zone. If SSH access on port 22 is needed, for example, run the following: \"sudo firewall-cmd --permanent --add-service=ssh --zone=drop\"\n\nReload the firewall rules to update the runtime configuration from the \"--permanent\" changes made above:\n$ sudo firewall-cmd --reload\n\nSet the default zone to the drop zone:\n$ sudo firewall-cmd --set-default-zone=drop\nNote: This is a runtime and permanent change.\n\nAdd any interfaces to the newly modified \"drop\" zone:\n$ sudo firewall-cmd --permanent --zone=drop --change-interface=ens33\n\nReload the firewall rules for changes to take effect:\n$ sudo firewall-cmd --reload","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 is configured to employ a deny-all, allow-by-exception policy for allowing connections to other systems with the following commands:\n\n$ sudo  firewall-cmd --state\nrunning\n\n$ sudo firewall-cmd --get-active-zones\npublic\n   interfaces: ens33\n\n$ sudo firewall-cmd --info-zone=public | grep target\n   target: DROP\n\n$ sudo firewall-cmd --permanent --info-zone=public | grep target\n   target: DROP\n\nIf no zones are active on the OL 9 interfaces or if runtime and permanent targets are set to a different option other than \"DROP\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Failure to restrict network connectivity only to authorized systems permits inbound connections from malicious systems. It also permits outbound connections that may facilitate exfiltration of DOD data.\n\nOL 9 incorporates the \"firewalld\" daemon, which allows for many different configurations. One of these configurations is zones. Zones can be used to a deny-all, allow-by-exception approach. The default \"drop\" zone will drop all incoming network packets unless it is explicitly allowed by the configuration file or is related to an outgoing network connection.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"9962","uuid":"570bab9b-0077-4ebb-bb45-9f7ad8523d6b","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C153BD2ED692A92FB3FBDEA2954B587866FE19D3\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'OL 9 must be configured so that the firewall employs a deny-all, allow-by-exception policy for allowing connections to other systems.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271474","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271474","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271474","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-271474r1091134_rule","rule_id":"SV-271474","rule_version":"OL09-00-000230","rule_title":"OL 9 must have the sudo package installed.","fix_text":"The sudo package can be installed with the following command:\n\n# dnf install -y sudo","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 has the sudo package installed with the following command:\n\n$ dnf list --installed sudo\nInstalled Packages\nsudo.x86_64                                          1.9.5p2-10.el9_3                                          @anaconda\n\nIf the sudo package is not installed, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"sudo is a program designed to allow a system administrator to give limited root privileges to users and log root activity. The basic philosophy is to give as few privileges as possible but still allow system users to complete their work.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"8076","uuid":"aa9f02df-4496-4622-a5e8-ebded65e5353","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-271475","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271475","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271475","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-271475r1091137_rule","rule_id":"SV-271475","rule_version":"OL09-00-000231","rule_title":"OL 9 must use the invoking user's password for privilege escalation when using sudo.","fix_text":"Configure OL 9 to use the invoking user's password for privilege escalation when using sudo. \n\nDefine the following in the Defaults section of the /etc/sudoers file or a single configuration file in the /etc/sudoers.d/ directory:\n\nDefaults !targetpw\nDefaults !rootpw\nDefaults !runaspw","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 is configured to enforce the sudoers security policy to use the invoking user's password for privilege escalation with the following command:\n\n$ sudo egrep -i '(!rootpw|!targetpw|!runaspw)' /etc/sudoers /etc/sudoers.d/* | grep -v '#'\n/etc/sudoers:Defaults !targetpw\n/etc/sudoers:Defaults !rootpw\n/etc/sudoers:Defaults !runaspw\n\nIf no results are returned, this is a finding.\n\nIf results are returned from more than one file location, this is a finding.\n\nIf \"Defaults !targetpw\" is not defined, this is a finding.\n\nIf \"Defaults !rootpw\" is not defined, this is a finding.\n\nIf \"Defaults !runaspw\" is not defined, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If the rootpw, targetpw, or runaspw flags are defined and not disabled, by default the operating system will prompt the invoking user for the \"root\" user password.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"2716","uuid":"c6a1cdf0-50b4-45ac-85a6-f0ec5185f050","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E50F65FDF98FEEA45EC96E6F0EB4016144337DD7\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'OL 9 must use the invoking user's password for privilege escalation when using sudo.' is not present or not in use on this the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271476","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271476","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271476","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-271476r1091140_rule","rule_id":"SV-271476","rule_version":"OL09-00-000232","rule_title":"OL 9 must restrict privilege elevation to authorized personnel.","fix_text":"Remove the following entries from the /etc/sudoers file or configuration file under /etc/sudoers.d/:\n\nALL     ALL=(ALL) ALL\nALL     ALL=(ALL:ALL) ALL","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 restricts privilege elevation to authorized personnel with the following command:\n\n$ sudo sh -c 'grep -iw ALL /etc/sudoers /etc/sudoers.d/*'\n\nIf the either of the following entries are returned, this is a finding:\nALL     ALL=(ALL) ALL\nALL     ALL=(ALL:ALL) ALL","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If the sudoers file is not configured correctly, any user defined on the system can initiate privileged actions on the target system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"2182","uuid":"950dca3f-f053-4c14-b83b-131f886e30b0","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D9316C2F9A155A77A5EB9DBD6014537586289B3B\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'OL 9 must restrict privilege elevation to authorized personnel.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271477","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271477","title":"SRG-OS-000396-GPOS-00176","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271477","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000396-GPOS-00176","rule_id_src":"SV-271477r1190784_rule","rule_id":"SV-271477","rule_version":"OL09-00-000240","rule_title":"OL 9 must have the crypto-policies package installed.","fix_text":"Install the crypto-policies package (if not already installed) with the following command:\n\n$ sudo dnf install -y crypto-policies","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the OL 9 crypto-policies package is installed with the following command:\n\n$ dnf list --installed crypto-policies\nInstalled Packages\ncrypto-policies.noarch                           20240202-1.git283706d.el9                            @ol9_baseos_latest\n\nIf the crypto-policies package is not installed, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Centralized cryptographic policies simplify applying secure ciphers across an operating system and the applications that run on that operating system. Use of weak or untested encryption algorithms undermines the purposes of using encryption to protect data.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000396-GPOS-00176, SRG-OS-000393-GPOS-00173, SRG-OS-000394-GPOS-00174","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002450","CCI-002890","CCI-003123"],"reference_identifier":"1552","uuid":"42ec6ede-b57a-45d9-b822-6494d12b0ce0","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 35FF0090ADA37A4F77C22B552E761081B471A823\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'OL 9 must have the crypto-policies package installed.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271478","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271478","title":"SRG-OS-000396-GPOS-00176","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271478","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000396-GPOS-00176","rule_id_src":"SV-271478r1190787_rule","rule_id":"SV-271478","rule_version":"OL09-00-000241","rule_title":"OL 9 must implement a FIPS 140-3 compliant systemwide cryptographic policy.","fix_text":"Configure OL 9 to use a modified FIPS-compliant systemwide crypto-policy.\n \nCreate subpolicies for enhancements to the systemwide crypto-policy with the following commands:\n \nCreate or edit the SCOPES-AND-WILDCARDS policy module in a text editor and insert options that modify the systemwide cryptographic policy as follows:\n\n$ sudo vi /etc/crypto-policies/policies/modules/SCOPES-AND-WILDCARDS.pmod\n \nAdd the following lines to the policy:\n\n# Disable CHACHA20-POLY1305 for the TLS protocol (OpenSSL, GnuTLS, NSS, and OpenJDK)\ncipher@TLS = -CHACHA20-POLY1305\n \n# Disable all CBC mode ciphers for the SSH protocol (libssh and OpenSSH):\n\ncipher@SSH = -*-CBC\n \nCreate or edit the OPENSSH-SUBPOLICY module in a text editor and insert options that modify the systemwide crypto-policy as follows:\n\n$ sudo vi /etc/crypto-policies/policies/modules/OPENSSH-SUBPOLICY.pmod\n \nAdd the following lines to the policy:\n\n# Define ciphers for OpenSSH\ncipher@SSH=AES-256-GCM AES-128-GCM AES-256-CTR AES-128-CTR\n \n# Define MACs for OpenSSH\nmac@SSH=HMAC-SHA2-512 HMAC-SHA2-256\n \nCreate or edit the REQUIRE.pmod file and add the following lines to include the subpolicies in the FIPS configuration with the following command:\n\n$ sudo vi /etc/crypto-policies/policies/modules/REQUIRE.pmod\n \nAdd the following lines to REQUIRE.pmod:\n\n@OPENSSH-SUBPOLICY\n@SCOPES-AND-WILDCARDS\n \nApply the policy enhancements to the FIPS systemwide cryptographic policy level with the following command:\n \n$ sudo update-crypto-policies --set FIPS\n\nNote: If additional subpolicies are being employed, they must be added to the REQUIRE.pmod as well. REQUIRE.pmod is included in the systemwide crypto-policy when it is set.\n \nTo make the cryptographic settings effective for already running services and applications, restart the system:\n\n$ sudo reboot","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify OL 9 is set to use a modified FIPS compliant systemwide crypto-policy.\n \n$ update-crypto-policies --show\nFIPS\n \nIf the systemwide crypto-policy is not set to \"FIPS\", this is a finding.\n\nNote: If subpolicies have been configured, they will be listed in a colon-separated list starting with FIPS as follows:\n\nFIPS:<SUBPOLICY-NAME>:<SUBPOLICY-NAME>.\n\nVerify the current minimum crypto-policy configuration with the following commands:\n \n$ grep -E 'rsa_size|hash' /etc/crypto-policies/state/CURRENT.pol\nhash = SHA2-256 SHA2-384 SHA2-512 SHA2-224 SHA3-256 SHA3-384 SHA3-512 SHAKE-256\nmin_rsa_size = 2048\n \nIf the \"hash\" values do not include at least the following FIPS 140-3-compliant algorithms, \"SHA2-256 SHA2-384 SHA2-512 SHA2-224 SHA3-256 SHA3-384 SHA3-512 SHAKE-256\", this is a finding.\n\nIf there are algorithms that include \"SHA1\" or a hash value less than \"256\", this is a finding.\n\nIf the \"min_rsa_size\" is not set to a value of at least 2048, this is a finding.\n \nIf these commands do not return any output, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Centralized cryptographic policies simplify applying secure ciphers across an operating system and the applications that run on that operating system. Use of weak or untested encryption algorithms undermines the purposes of using encryption to protect data.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000396-GPOS-00176, SRG-OS-000393-GPOS-00173, SRG-OS-000394-GPOS-00174","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002450","CCI-002890","CCI-003123"],"reference_identifier":"8669","uuid":"e0a5f3bc-3ed7-4334-85b7-cd2b42c77cc5","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9544DB490BF122524ADBA7D402BA29924851B2E5\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'OL 9 must implement a FIPS 140-3 compliant systemwide cryptographic policy.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271479","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271479","title":"SRG-OS-000396-GPOS-00176","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271479","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000396-GPOS-00176","rule_id_src":"SV-271479r1184180_rule","rule_id":"SV-271479","rule_version":"OL09-00-000242","rule_title":"OL 9 must not allow the cryptographic policy to be overridden.","fix_text":"Configure OL 9 to correctly implement the systemwide cryptographic policies by reinstalling the crypto-policies package contents.\n\nReinstall crypto-policies with the following command:\n\n$ sudo dnf -y reinstall crypto-policies\n\nSet the crypto-policy to FIPS with the following command:\n\n$ sudo update-crypto-policies --set FIPS\n\nSetting system policy to FIPS\n\nNote: Systemwide crypto policies are applied on application startup. It is recommended to restart the system for the change of policies to fully take place.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify OL 9 cryptographic policies are not overridden.\n\nVerify the configured policy matches the generated policy with the following command:\n\n$ sudo update-crypto-policies --check && echo PASS\nThe configured policy matches the generated policy\nPASS\n\nIf the last line is not \"PASS\", this is a finding.\n\nList all of the crypto backends configured on the system with the following command:\n\n$ ls -l /etc/crypto-policies/back-ends/ \nlrwxrwxrwx. 1 root root  40 Nov 13 16:29 bind.config -> /usr/share/crypto-policies/FIPS/bind.txt\nlrwxrwxrwx. 1 root root  42 Nov 13 16:29 gnutls.config -> /usr/share/crypto-policies/FIPS/gnutls.txt\nlrwxrwxrwx. 1 root root  40 Nov 13 16:29 java.config -> /usr/share/crypto-policies/FIPS/java.txt\nlrwxrwxrwx. 1 root root  46 Nov 13 16:29 javasystem.config -> /usr/share/crypto-policies/FIPS/javasystem.txt\nlrwxrwxrwx. 1 root root  40 Nov 13 16:29 krb5.config -> /usr/share/crypto-policies/FIPS/krb5.txt\nlrwxrwxrwx. 1 root root  45 Nov 13 16:29 libreswan.config -> /usr/share/crypto-policies/FIPS/libreswan.txt\nlrwxrwxrwx. 1 root root  42 Nov 13 16:29 libssh.config -> /usr/share/crypto-policies/FIPS/libssh.txt\n-rw-r--r--. 1 root root 398 Nov 13 16:29 nss.config\nlrwxrwxrwx. 1 root root  43 Nov 13 16:29 openssh.config -> /usr/share/crypto-policies/FIPS/openssh.txt\nlrwxrwxrwx. 1 root root  49 Nov 13 16:29 opensshserver.config -> /usr/share/crypto-policies/FIPS/opensshserver.txt\nlrwxrwxrwx. 1 root root  46 Nov 13 16:29 opensslcnf.config -> /usr/share/crypto-policies/FIPS/opensslcnf.txt\nlrwxrwxrwx. 1 root root  43 Nov 13 16:29 openssl.config -> /usr/share/crypto-policies/FIPS/openssl.txt\nlrwxrwxrwx. 1 root root  48 Nov 13 16:29 openssl_fips.config -> /usr/share/crypto-policies/FIPS/openssl_fips.txt\n\nIf the paths do not point to the respective files under /usr/share/crypto-policies/FIPS path, this is a finding.\n\nNote: nss.config should not be hyperlinked.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Centralized cryptographic policies simplify applying secure ciphers across an operating system and the applications that run on that operating system. Use of weak or untested encryption algorithms undermines the purposes of using encryption to protect data.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000396-GPOS-00176, SRG-OS-000393-GPOS-00173, SRG-OS-000394-GPOS-00174","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002450","CCI-002890","CCI-003123"],"reference_identifier":"4175","uuid":"b809db9e-1392-4a83-86a9-8e481640d792","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: EEA83C725E803682637546B0B171F5327C77529A\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'OL 9 must not allow the cryptographic policy to be overridden.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271480","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271480","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271480","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-271480r1091152_rule","rule_id":"SV-271480","rule_version":"OL09-00-000243","rule_title":"OL 9 must be configured so that the cryptographic hashes of system files match vendor values.","fix_text":"Configure OL 9 so that the cryptographic hashes of system files match vendor values.\n\nGiven output from the check command, identify the package that provides the output and reinstall it. The following trimmed example output shows a package that has failed verification, been identified, and been reinstalled:\n\n$ sudo rpm -Va --noconfig | awk '$1 ~ /..5/ && $2 != \"c\"'\nS.5....T.    /usr/bin/znew\n\n$ sudo dnf provides /usr/bin/znew\n[...]\ngzip-1.10-8.el9.x86_64 : The GNU data compression program\n[...]\n\n$ sudo dnf -y reinstall gzip\n[...]\n\n$ sudo rpm -Va --noconfig | awk '$1 ~ /..5/ && $2 != \"c\"'\n[no output]","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 is configured so that the cryptographic hashes of system files match vendor values.\n \nList files on the system that have file hashes different from what is expected by the RPM database with the following command:\n\n$ sudo rpm -Va --noconfig | awk '$1 ~ /..5/ && $2 != \"c\"' \n\nIf there is output, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The hashes of important files like system executables should match the information given by the RPM database. Executables with erroneous hashes could be a sign of nefarious activity on the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"2476","uuid":"98f94849-6777-4acb-94d7-32442e7d30c6","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 86E816A4318250EF969EF7420ED308768361838E\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'OL 9 must be configured so that the cryptographic hashes of system files match vendor values.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271482","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271482","title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271482","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","rule_id_src":"SV-271482r1091158_rule","rule_id":"SV-271482","rule_version":"OL09-00-000250","rule_title":"OL 9 networked systems must have SSH installed.","fix_text":"The openssh-server package can be installed with the following command:\n \n$ sudo dnf install -y openssh-server","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 has the openssh-server package installed with the following command:\n\n$ dnf list --installed openssh-server\nInstalled Packages\nopenssh-server.x86_64                              8.7p1-38.0.2.el9_4.4                               @ol9_baseos_latest\n\nIf the \"openssh-server\" package is not installed, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Without protection of the transmitted information, confidentiality and integrity may be compromised because unprotected communications can be intercepted and either read or altered. \n\nThis requirement applies to both internal and external networks and all types of information system components from which information can be transmitted (e.g., servers, mobile devices, notebook computers, printers, copiers, scanners, and facsimile machines). Communication paths outside the physical protection of a controlled boundary are exposed to the possibility of interception and modification. \n\nProtecting the confidentiality and integrity of organizational information can be accomplished by physical means (e.g., employing physical distribution systems) or by logical means (e.g., employing cryptographic techniques). If physical means of protection are employed, then logical means (cryptography) do not have to be employed, and vice versa.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187, SRG-OS-000424-GPOS-00188, SRG-OS-000425-GPOS-00189, SRG-OS-000426-GPOS-00190","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002418","CCI-002421","CCI-002420","CCI-002422"],"reference_identifier":"4704","uuid":"ae00ccad-bb6a-4fda-b950-ba3da6e94693","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D8533314D8146939DB2713B96134AA76CA799965\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'OL 9 networked systems must have SSH installed.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271483","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271483","title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271483","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","rule_id_src":"SV-271483r1091161_rule","rule_id":"SV-271483","rule_version":"OL09-00-000251","rule_title":"OL 9 networked systems must have and implement SSH to protect the confidentiality and integrity of transmitted and received information, as well as information during preparation for transmission.","fix_text":"Enable the sshd service with the following command:\n\n$ systemctl enable --now sshd","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 networked systems implement SSH to protect the confidentiality and integrity of transmitted and received information, as well as information during preparation for transmission.\n\nVerify that \"sshd\" is active with the following command:\n\n$ systemctl is-active sshd\nactive\n\nIf the \"sshd\" service is not active, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Without protection of the transmitted information, confidentiality and integrity may be compromised because unprotected communications can be intercepted and either read or altered. \n\nThis requirement applies to both internal and external networks and all types of information system components from which information can be transmitted (e.g., servers, mobile devices, notebook computers, printers, copiers, scanners, and facsimile machines). Communication paths outside the physical protection of a controlled boundary are exposed to the possibility of interception and modification. \n\nProtecting the confidentiality and integrity of organizational information can be accomplished by physical means (e.g., employing physical distribution systems) or by logical means (e.g., employing cryptographic techniques). If physical means of protection are employed, then logical means (cryptography) do not have to be employed, and vice versa.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187, SRG-OS-000424-GPOS-00188, SRG-OS-000425-GPOS-00189, SRG-OS-000426-GPOS-00190","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002418","CCI-002421","CCI-002420","CCI-002422"],"reference_identifier":"1194","uuid":"3cb8a6d9-2fa8-4cf3-962a-bc7d00ad1a07","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-271485","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271485","title":"SRG-OS-000250-GPOS-00093","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271485","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000250-GPOS-00093","rule_id_src":"SV-271485r1184186_rule","rule_id":"SV-271485","rule_version":"OL09-00-000254","rule_title":"OL 9 SSH server must be configured to use only ciphers employing FIPS 140-3 validated cryptographic hash algorithms to protect the confidentiality of SSH server connections.","fix_text":"Configure the OL 9 SSH server to use only ciphers employing FIPS 140-3 approved algorithms.\n\nReinstall crypto-policies with the following command:\n\n$ sudo dnf -y reinstall crypto-policies\n\nSet the crypto-policy to FIPS with the following command:\n\n$ sudo update-crypto-policies --set FIPS\n\nSetting system policy to FIPS\n\nNote: Systemwide crypto policies are applied on application startup. It is recommended to restart the system for the change of policies to fully take place.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify OL 9 SSH server is configured to use only ciphers employing FIPS 140-3 approved algorithms.\n\nTo verify the ciphers in the systemwide SSH configuration file, use the following command:\n\n$ sudo grep -i Ciphers /etc/crypto-policies/back-ends/opensshserver.config \nCiphers aes256-gcm@openssh.com,aes256-ctr,aes128-gcm@openssh.com,aes128-ctr\n\nIf the cipher entries in the \"opensshserver.config\" file have any ciphers other than \"aes256-gcm@openssh.com,aes256-ctr,aes128-gcm@openssh.com,aes128-ctr\", or they are missing or commented out, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Without cryptographic integrity protections, information can be altered by unauthorized users without detection.\n\nRemote access (e.g., RDP) is access to DOD nonpublic information systems by an authorized user (or an information system) communicating through an external, nonorganization-controlled network. Remote access methods include, for example, dial-up, broadband, and wireless.\n\nCryptographic mechanisms used for protecting the integrity of information include, for example, signed hash functions using asymmetric cryptography enabling distribution of the public key to verify the hash information while maintaining the confidentiality of the secret key used to generate the hash.\n\nOL 9 incorporates systemwide crypto policies by default. The SSH configuration file has no effect on the ciphers, MACs, or algorithms unless specifically defined in the /etc/sysconfig/sshd file. The employed algorithms can be viewed in the /etc/crypto-policies/back-ends/opensshserver.config file.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001453"],"reference_identifier":"8968","uuid":"2932ab89-0d7c-431c-8562-bfe4dc478c73","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D930C3A3E5F86FF68B096105D83713CD1F8BBF5E\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'OL 9 SSH server must be configured to use only ciphers employing FIPS 140-3 validated cryptographic hash algorithms to protect the confidentiality of SSH server connections.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271486","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271486","title":"SRG-OS-000250-GPOS-00093","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271486","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000250-GPOS-00093","rule_id_src":"SV-271486r1184188_rule","rule_id":"SV-271486","rule_version":"OL09-00-000255","rule_title":"OL 9 SSH server must be configured to use only Message Authentication Codes (MACs) employing FIPS 140-3 validated cryptographic hash algorithms to protect the confidentiality of SSH server connections.","fix_text":"Configure the OL 9 SSH server to use only MACs employing FIPS 140-3 approved algorithms.\n\nReinstall crypto-policies with the following command:\n\n$ sudo dnf -y reinstall crypto-policies\n\nSet the crypto-policy to FIPS with the following command:\n\n$ sudo update-crypto-policies --set FIPS\n\nSetting system policy to FIPS\n\nNote: Systemwide crypto policies are applied on application startup. It is recommended to restart the system for the change of policies to fully take place.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify OL 9 SSH server is configured to use only MACs employing FIPS 140-3 approved algorithms.\n\nTo verify the MACs in the systemwide SSH configuration file, use the following command:\n\n$ sudo grep -i MACs /etc/crypto-policies/back-ends/opensshserver.config\nMACs hmac-sha2-256-etm@openssh.com,hmac-sha2-512-etm@openssh.com,hmac-sha2-256,hmac-sha2-512\n\nIf the MACs entries in the \"opensshserver.config\" file have any hashes other than \"hmac-sha2-256-etm@openssh.com,hmac-sha2-512-etm@openssh.com,hmac-sha2-256,hmac-sha2-512\", or they are missing or commented out, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Without cryptographic integrity protections, information can be altered by unauthorized users without detection.\n\nRemote access (e.g., RDP) is access to DOD nonpublic information systems by an authorized user (or an information system) communicating through an external, nonorganization-controlled network. Remote access methods include, for example, dial-up, broadband, and wireless.\n\nCryptographic mechanisms used for protecting the integrity of information include, for example, signed hash functions using asymmetric cryptography enabling distribution of the public key to verify the hash information while maintaining the confidentiality of the secret key used to generate the hash.\n\nOL 9 incorporates systemwide crypto policies by default. The SSH configuration file has no effect on the ciphers, MACs, or algorithms unless specifically defined in the /etc/sysconfig/sshd file. The employed algorithms can be viewed in the /etc/crypto-policies/back-ends/opensshserver.config file.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001453"],"reference_identifier":"5127","uuid":"db474b99-cc92-403a-9e54-528fe4f747fe","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-271487","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271487","title":"SRG-OS-000023-GPOS-00006","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271487","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000023-GPOS-00006","rule_id_src":"SV-271487r1091173_rule","rule_id":"SV-271487","rule_version":"OL09-00-000256","rule_title":"OL 9 must display the Standard Mandatory DOD Notice and Consent Banner before granting local or remote access to the system via a SSH logon.","fix_text":"Configure OL 9 to display the Standard Mandatory DOD Notice and Consent Banner before granting access to the system via ssh.\n\nEdit the \"etc/ssh/sshd_config\" file or a file in \"/etc/ssh/sshd_config.d\" to uncomment the banner keyword and configure it to point to a file that will contain the logon banner (this file may be named differently or be in a different location if using a version of SSH that is provided by a third-party vendor).\n\nAn example configuration line is:\n\nBanner /etc/issue","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 displays the Standard Mandatory DOD Notice and Consent Banner before granting access to the system via SSH connections.\n\nCheck for the location of the banner file currently being used with the following command:\n\n$ sudo /usr/sbin/sshd -dd 2>&1 | awk '/filename/ {print $4}' | tr -d '\\r' | tr '\\n' ' ' | xargs sudo grep -iH '^\\s*banner'\nbanner /etc/issue\n\nIf the line is commented out or if the file is missing, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The warning message reinforces policy awareness during the logon process and facilitates possible legal action against attackers. Alternatively, systems whose ownership should not be obvious should ensure usage of a banner that does not provide easy attribution.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000023-GPOS-00006, SRG-OS-000228-GPOS-00088","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000048","CCI-001384","CCI-001385","CCI-001386","CCI-001387","CCI-001388"],"reference_identifier":"6283","uuid":"cc479d8f-204b-4128-9898-cb504afc0739","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 97B4012AA2D2B5FC9F3E8831CDA08EE5F10E4C91\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'OL 9 must display the Standard Mandatory DOD Notice and Consent Banner before granting local or remote access to the system via a SSH logon.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271488","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271488","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271488","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-271488r1091176_rule","rule_id":"SV-271488","rule_version":"OL09-00-000260","rule_title":"OL 9 must have the openssh-clients package installed.","fix_text":"Install the openssh-clients package with the following command:\n \n$ sudo dnf install -y openssh-clients","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 has the openssh-clients package installed with the following command:\n\n$ dnf list --installed openssh-clients\nInstalled Packages\nopenssh-clients.x86_64                          8.7p1-38.0.2.el9_4.4                          @ol9_baseos_latest\n\nIf the openssh-clients package is not installed, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This package includes utilities to make encrypted connections and transfer files securely to SSH servers.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"9386","uuid":"5be72f33-8f2b-4c12-bb58-7ee098fb9cac","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FD53556A75F0878673FB4A4653F0F397DAED64E2\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'OL 9 must have the openssh-clients package installed.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271489","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271489","title":"SRG-OS-000250-GPOS-00093","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271489","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000250-GPOS-00093","rule_id_src":"SV-271489r1184190_rule","rule_id":"SV-271489","rule_version":"OL09-00-000261","rule_title":"OL 9 SSH client must be configured to use only DOD-approved encryption ciphers employing FIPS 140-3 validated cryptographic hash algorithms to protect the confidentiality of SSH client connections.","fix_text":"Configure the SSH client to use only ciphers employing FIPS 140-3 approved algorithms.\n\nReinstall crypto-policies with the following command:\n\n$ sudo dnf -y reinstall crypto-policies\n\nSet the crypto-policy to FIPS with the following command:\n\n$ sudo update-crypto-policies --set FIPS\n\nSetting system policy to FIPS\n\nNote: Systemwide crypto policies are applied on application startup. It is recommended to restart the system for the change of policies to fully take place.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify OL 9 is configured so that the SSH client uses only ciphers employing FIPS 140-3 approved algorithms.\n\nTo verify the ciphers in the systemwide SSH configuration file, use the following command:\n\n$ grep -i Ciphers /etc/crypto-policies/back-ends/openssh.config \nCiphers aes256-gcm@openssh.com,aes256-ctr,aes128-gcm@openssh.com,aes128-ctr\n\nIf the cipher entries in the \"openssh.config\" file have any ciphers other than \"aes256-gcm@openssh.com,aes256-ctr,aes128-gcm@openssh.com,aes128-ctr\", or they are missing or commented out, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Without cryptographic integrity protections, information can be altered by unauthorized users without detection.\n\nRemote access (e.g., RDP) is access to DOD nonpublic information systems by an authorized user (or an information system) communicating through an external, nonorganization-controlled network. Remote access methods include, for example, dial-up, broadband, and wireless.\n\nCryptographic mechanisms used for protecting the integrity of information include, for example, signed hash functions using asymmetric cryptography enabling distribution of the public key to verify the hash information while maintaining the confidentiality of the secret key used to generate the hash.\n\nOL 9 incorporates systemwide crypto policies by default. The SSH configuration file has no effect on the ciphers, MACs, or algorithms unless specifically defined in the /etc/sysconfig/sshd file. The employed algorithms can be viewed in the /etc/crypto-policies/back-ends/opensshserver.config file.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001453"],"reference_identifier":"8375","uuid":"3c24d3c1-c46d-456b-9c66-dbee9ceb0f45","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 92C9875417E82911ED2F0E62A77BD8DB1117F2FB\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'OL 9 SSH client must be configured to use only DOD-approved encryption ciphers employing FIPS 140-3 validated cryptographic hash algorithms to protect the confidentiality of SSH client connections.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271490","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271490","title":"SRG-OS-000250-GPOS-00093","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271490","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000250-GPOS-00093","rule_id_src":"SV-271490r1184192_rule","rule_id":"SV-271490","rule_version":"OL09-00-000262","rule_title":"OL 9 SSH client must be configured to use only DOD-approved Message Authentication Codes (MACs) employing FIPS 140-3 validated cryptographic hash algorithms to protect the confidentiality of SSH client connections.","fix_text":"Configure the SSH client to use only MACs employing FIPS 140-3 approved algorithms.\n\nReinstall crypto-policies with the following command:\n\n$ sudo dnf -y reinstall crypto-policies\n\nSet the crypto-policy to FIPS with the following command:\n\n$ sudo update-crypto-policies --set FIPS\n\nSetting system policy to FIPS\n\nNote: Systemwide crypto policies are applied on application startup. It is recommended to restart the system for the change of policies to fully take place.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify OL 9 is configured so that the SSH client uses only MACs employing FIPS 140-3 approved algorithms.\n\nTo verify the MACs in the systemwide SSH configuration file, use the following command:\n\n$ grep -i MACs /etc/crypto-policies/back-ends/openssh.config\nMACs hmac-sha2-256-etm@openssh.com,hmac-sha2-512-etm@openssh.com,hmac-sha2-256,hmac-sha2-512\n\nIf the MACs entries in the \"openssh.config\" file have any hashes other than \"hmac-sha2-256-etm@openssh.com,hmac-sha2-512-etm@openssh.com,hmac-sha2-256,hmac-sha2-512\", or they are missing or commented out, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Without cryptographic integrity protections, information can be altered by unauthorized users without detection.\n\nRemote access (e.g., RDP) is access to DOD nonpublic information systems by an authorized user (or an information system) communicating through an external, nonorganization-controlled network. Remote access methods include, for example, dial-up, broadband, and wireless.\n\nCryptographic mechanisms used for protecting the integrity of information include, for example, signed hash functions using asymmetric cryptography enabling distribution of the public key to verify the hash information while maintaining the confidentiality of the secret key used to generate the hash.\n\nOL 9 incorporates systemwide crypto policies by default. The SSH configuration file has no effect on the ciphers, MACs, or algorithms unless specifically defined in the /etc/sysconfig/sshd file. The employed algorithms can be viewed in the /etc/crypto-policies/back-ends/opensshserver.config file.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001453"],"reference_identifier":"8608","uuid":"665609b5-c06c-44cd-a6e6-e81c567112ff","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D6ACAC87F7B90804013099D511C0A1A3A7CFAE05\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'OL 9 SSH client must be configured to use only DOD-approved Message Authentication Codes (MACs) employing FIPS 140-3 validated cryptographic hash algorithms to protect the confidentiality of SSH client connections.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271491","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271491","title":"SRG-OS-000105-GPOS-00052","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271491","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000105-GPOS-00052","rule_id_src":"SV-271491r1091185_rule","rule_id":"SV-271491","rule_version":"OL09-00-000270","rule_title":"OL 9 must have the openssl-pkcs11 package installed.","fix_text":"Install the openssl-pkcs11 package with the following command:\n \n$ sudo dnf install -y openssl-pkcs11","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 has the openssl-pkcs11 package installed with the following command:\n\n$ dnf list --installed openssl-pkcs11\nInstalled Packages\nopenssl-pkcs11.x86_64                                  0.4.11-9.el9                                   @ol9_baseos_latest\n\nIf the \"openssl-pkcs11\" package is not installed, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Without the use of multifactor authentication, the ease of access to privileged functions is greatly increased. Multifactor authentication requires using two or more factors to achieve authentication. A privileged account is defined as an information system account with authorizations of a privileged user. The DOD CAC with DOD-approved PKI is an example of multifactor authentication.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000105-GPOS-00052, SRG-OS-000375-GPOS-00160, SRG-OS-000376-GPOS-00161, SRG-OS-000377-GPOS-00162","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000765","CCI-004046","CCI-001953","CCI-001954"],"reference_identifier":"2166","uuid":"fb806e36-12f5-4b16-864d-c1d42fd25b22","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 5E7D6FF06A1450008BE996CE4C6661CF5BF48DC7\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'OL 9 must have the openssl-pkcs11 package installed.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271493","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271493","title":"SRG-OS-000705-GPOS-00150","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271493","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000705-GPOS-00150","rule_id_src":"SV-271493r1091191_rule","rule_id":"SV-271493","rule_version":"OL09-00-000285","rule_title":"OL 9 must have the SSSD package installed.","fix_text":"Install the SSSD package with the following command:\n\n$ sudo dnf install -y sssd","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 has the SSSD package installed with the following command:\n\n$ dnf list --installed sssd\nInstalled Packages\nsssd.x86_64                                    2.9.5-4.0.1.el9_5.1                                    @ol9_baseos_latest\n\nIf the SSSD package is not installed, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Using an authentication device, such as a CAC or token that is separate from the information system, ensures that even if the information system is compromised, that compromise will not affect credentials stored on the authentication device. \n \nMultifactor solutions that require devices separate from information systems gaining access include, for example, hardware tokens providing time-based or challenge-response authenticators and smart cards such as the U.S. Government Personal Identity Verification card and the DOD Common Access Card. \n \nA privileged account is defined as an information system account with authorizations of a privileged user. \n \nRemote access is access to DOD nonpublic information systems by an authorized user (or an information system) communicating through an external, nonorganization-controlled network. Remote access methods include, for example, dial-up, broadband, and wireless. \n \nThis requirement only applies to components where this is specific to the function of the device or has the concept of an organizational user (e.g., VPN, proxy capability). This does not apply to authentication for the purpose of configuring the device itself (management).\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000705-GPOS-00150, SRG-OS-000105-GPOS-00052, SRG-OS-000106-GPOS-00053, SRG-OS-000107-GPOS-00054, SRG-OS-000108-GPOS-00055, SRG-OS-000375-GPOS-00160","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-004046","CCI-004047","CCI-000765","CCI-000766"],"reference_identifier":"9459","uuid":"4966e784-034f-4473-9378-66eeea3947d8","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: B8D802C1BD6BE7B76A00153C169F30F08A9118C4\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'OL 9 must have the SSSD package installed.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271494","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271494","title":"SRG-OS-000705-GPOS-00150","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271494","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000705-GPOS-00150","rule_id_src":"SV-271494r1091194_rule","rule_id":"SV-271494","rule_version":"OL09-00-000286","rule_title":"OL 9 must use the SSSD package for multifactor authentication services.","fix_text":"Configure the sssd.service to start automatically on reboot with the following command: \n \n$ sudo systemctl enable sssd.service \n \nEnsure the sssd service is running: \n \n$ sudo systemctl start sssd.service","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 is configured so that the sssd.service is enabled and active with the following commands: \n \n$ sudo systemctl is-enabled sssd\nenabled\n\n$ sudo systemctl is-active sssd\nactive\n\nIf sssd.service is not active or enabled, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Using an authentication device, such as a CAC or token that is separate from the information system, ensures that even if the information system is compromised, that compromise will not affect credentials stored on the authentication device. \n \nMultifactor solutions that require devices separate from information systems gaining access include, for example, hardware tokens providing time-based or challenge-response authenticators and smart cards such as the U.S. Government Personal Identity Verification card and the DOD Common Access Card. \n \nA privileged account is defined as an information system account with authorizations of a privileged user. \n \nWithout the use of multifactor authentication, the ease of access to privileged functions is greatly increased. \n \nMultifactor authentication requires using two or more factors to achieve authentication. \n \nFactors include:  \n1) Something a user knows (e.g., password/PIN); \n2) Something a user has (e.g., cryptographic identification device, token); and \n3) Something a user is (e.g., biometric). \n \nA privileged account is defined as an information system account with authorizations of a privileged user. \n \nNetwork access is defined as access to an information system by a user (or a process acting on behalf of a user) communicating through a network (e.g., local area network, wide area network, or the internet). \n \nThe DOD common access card (CAC) with DOD-approved PKI is an example of multifactor authentication.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000705-GPOS-00150, SRG-OS-000105-GPOS-00052, SRG-OS-000106-GPOS-00053, SRG-OS-000107-GPOS-00054, SRG-OS-000108-GPOS-00055, SRG-OS-000375-GPOS-00161","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-004046","CCI-004047","CCI-000765","CCI-000767"],"reference_identifier":"5855","uuid":"769bcd6f-c363-4290-b052-794796cbdda7","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: CCF2DC4CF47541BAF5DCC5F8BE4671F460149CAB\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'OL 9 must use the SSSD package for multifactor authentication services.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271495","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271495","title":"SRG-OS-000363-GPOS-00150","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271495","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000363-GPOS-00150","rule_id_src":"SV-271495r1091197_rule","rule_id":"SV-271495","rule_version":"OL09-00-000290","rule_title":"OL 9 must have the s-nail package installed.","fix_text":"Install the s-nail package with the following command:\n\n$ sudo dnf install -y s-nail","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 has the s-nail package installed on the system with the following command:\n\n$ dnf list --installed s-nail\nInstalled Packages\ns-nail.x86_64                                        14.9.22-6.el9                                        @ol9_appstream\n\nIf the s-nail package is not installed, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The s-nail package provides the mail command required to allow sending email notifications of unauthorized configuration changes to designated personnel.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001744"],"reference_identifier":"3951","uuid":"8e650709-8608-4bdc-b32d-d7dfab7677b5","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FC16C1DB6A7BF8A628F28865F3AB38C76FF4D81A\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'OL 9 must have the s-nail package installed.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271496","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271496","title":"SRG-OS-000363-GPOS-00150","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271496","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000363-GPOS-00150","rule_id_src":"SV-271496r1091200_rule","rule_id":"SV-271496","rule_version":"OL09-00-000300","rule_title":"OL 9 must have the Advanced Intrusion Detection Environment (AIDE) package installed.","fix_text":"Install AIDE, initialize it, and perform a manual check.\n\nInstall AIDE:\n\n$ sudo dnf install -y aide\n\nInitialize AIDE:\n     \n$ sudo /usr/sbin/aide --init\n\nExample output:\n\nStart timestamp: 2023-06-05 10:09:04 -0600 (AIDE 0.16)\nAIDE initialized database at /var/lib/aide/aide.db.new.gz\n\nNumber of entries:      86833\n\n---------------------------------------------------\nThe attributes of the (uncompressed) database(s):\n---------------------------------------------------\n\n/var/lib/aide/aide.db.new.gz\n  MD5      : coZUtPHhoFoeD7+k54fUvQ==\n  SHA1     : DVpOEMWJwo0uPgrKZAygIUgSxeM=\n  SHA256   : EQiZH0XNEk001tcDmJa+5STFEjDb4MPE\n             TGdBJ/uvZKc=\n  SHA512   : 86KUqw++PZhoPK0SZvT3zuFq9yu9nnPP\n             toei0nENVELJ1LPurjoMlRig6q69VR8l\n             +44EwO9eYyy9nnbzQsfG1g==\n\nEnd timestamp: 2023-06-05 10:09:57 -0600 (run time: 0m 53s)\n\nThe new database will need to be renamed to be read by AIDE:\n\n$ sudo mv /var/lib/aide/aide.db.new.gz /var/lib/aide/aide.db.gz\n\nPerform a manual check:\n\n$ sudo /usr/sbin/aide --check\n\nExample output:\n\n2023-06-05 10:16:08 -0600 (AIDE 0.16)\nAIDE found NO differences between database and filesystem. Looks okay!!","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 has the package installed with the following command:\n\n$ dnf list --installed aide\nInstalled Packages\naide.x86_64                                         0.16-100.el9                                          @ol9_appstream\n\nIf AIDE is not installed, ask the system administrator (SA) how file integrity checks are performed on the system. \n\nIf there is no application installed to perform integrity checks, this is a finding.\n\nIf AIDE is installed, check if it has been initialized with the following command:\n\n$ sudo /usr/sbin/aide --check\n\nIf the output is \"Couldn't open file /var/lib/aide/aide.db.gz for reading\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Without verification of the security functions, security functions may not operate correctly, and the failure may go unnoticed. Security function is defined as the hardware, software, and/or firmware of the information system responsible for enforcing the system security policy and supporting the isolation of code and data on which the protection is based. Security functionality includes, but is not limited to, establishing system accounts, configuring access authorizations (i.e., permissions, privileges), setting events to be audited, and setting intrusion detection parameters.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000363-GPOS-00150, SRG-OS-000445-GPOS-00199","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001744","CCI-002696"],"reference_identifier":"5387","uuid":"672ad1fe-d4ab-48e4-a710-f25860cd0b41","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 3D25246FCDD557C9BD7E178C81A2B05B3D89B4DA\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'OL 9 must have the Advanced Intrusion Detection Environment (AIDE) package installed.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271497","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271497","title":"SRG-OS-000363-GPOS-00150","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271497","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000363-GPOS-00150","rule_id_src":"SV-271497r1092471_rule","rule_id":"SV-271497","rule_version":"OL09-00-000301","rule_title":"OL 9 must routinely check the baseline configuration for unauthorized changes and notify the system administrator (SA) when anomalies in the operation of any security functions are discovered.","fix_text":"Configure the file integrity tool to run automatically on the system at least weekly and to notify designated personnel if baseline configurations are changed in an unauthorized manner. The AIDE tool can be configured to email designated personnel with the use of the cron system.\n \nThe following example output is generic. It will set cron to run AIDE daily and to send email at the completion of the analysis.\n\n$ sudo more /etc/cron.daily/aide\n \n#!/bin/bash\n/usr/sbin/aide --check | /bin/mail -s \"$HOSTNAME - Daily aide integrity check run\" root@sysname.mil\n\n$ sudo chmod 755  /etc/cron.daily/aide\n\n$ sudo crontab -e \n30 04 * * * root usr/sbin/aide","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 routinely executes a file integrity scan for changes to the system baseline. The command used in the example will use a daily occurrence.\n\nCheck the cron directories for scripts controlling the execution and notification of results of the file integrity application. For example, if Advanced Intrusion Detection Environment (AIDE) is installed on the system, use the following commands:\n\n$ ls -al /etc/cron.* | grep aide\n-rwxr-xr-x 1 root root 29 Nov 22 2015 aide\n\n$ sudo grep aide /etc/crontab /var/spool/cron/root\n/etc/crontab: 30 04 * * * root usr/sbin/aide\n/var/spool/cron/root: 30 04 * * * root usr/sbin/aide\n\n$ more /etc/cron.daily/aide\n#!/bin/bash\n/usr/sbin/aide --check | /bin/mail -s \"$HOSTNAME - Daily aide integrity check run\" root@sysname.mil\n\nIf the file integrity application does not exist, or a script file controlling the execution of the file integrity application does not exist, or the file integrity application does not notify designated personnel of changes, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unauthorized changes to the baseline configuration could make the system vulnerable to various attacks or allow unauthorized access to the operating system. Changes to operating system configurations can have unintended side effects, some of which may be relevant to security.\n\nDetecting such changes and providing an automated response can help avoid unintended, negative consequences that could ultimately affect the security state of the operating system. The operating system's information management officer (IMO)/information system security officer (ISSO) and SAs must be notified via email and/or monitoring system trap when there is an unauthorized modification of a configuration item.\n\nNotifications provided by information systems include messages to local computer consoles, and/or hardware indications, such as lights.\n\nThis capability must take into account operational requirements for availability for selecting an appropriate response. The organization may choose to shut down or restart the information system upon security function anomaly detection.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000363-GPOS-00150, SRG-OS-000446-GPOS-00200, SRG-OS-000447-GPOS-00201","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001744","CCI-002699","CCI-002702"],"reference_identifier":"4550","uuid":"b529a6de-5f86-4a6f-ab7a-b0fe793af95f","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7A10AFCE3B3D20A0419BB3B2E6775B87C7610677\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'OL 9 must routinely check the baseline configuration for unauthorized changes and notify the system administrator (SA) when anomalies in the operation of any security functions are discovered.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271498","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271498","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271498","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-271498r1091206_rule","rule_id":"SV-271498","rule_version":"OL09-00-000302","rule_title":"OL 9 must use a file integrity tool that is configured to use FIPS 140-3-approved cryptographic hashes for validating file contents and directories.","fix_text":"Configure the file integrity tool to use FIPS 140-3 cryptographic hashes for validating file and directory contents. \n\nIf AIDE is installed, ensure the \"sha512\" rule is present on all uncommented file and directory selection lists. Exclude any log files, or files expected to change frequently, to reduce unnecessary notifications.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 uses a file integrity tool that is configured to use FIPS 140-3-approved cryptographic hashes for validating file contents and directories.\n\nVerify that AIDE is configured to use FIPS 140-3 file hashing with the following command:\n\n$ sudo grep sha512 /etc/aide.conf \nAll=p+i+n+u+g+s+m+S+sha512+acl+xattrs+selinux\n\nIf the \"sha512\" rule is not being used on all uncommented selection lines in the \"/etc/aide.conf\" file, or another file integrity tool is not using FIPS 140-3-approved cryptographic hashes for validating file contents and directories, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"OL 9 installation media ships with an optional file integrity tool called Advanced Intrusion Detection Environment (AIDE). AIDE is highly configurable at install time. This requirement assumes the \"aide.conf\" file is under the \"/etc\" directory.\n\nFile integrity tools use cryptographic hashes for verifying file contents and directories have not been altered. These hashes must be FIPS 140-3-approved cryptographic hashes.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"9271","uuid":"61581e0a-d317-418c-9521-52adffa6821a","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A515159F59F2E082EB7EA38135D95537AEAFD6D0\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'OL 9 must use a file integrity tool that is configured to use FIPS 140-3-approved cryptographic hashes for validating file contents and directories.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271499","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271499","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271499","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-271499r1091209_rule","rule_id":"SV-271499","rule_version":"OL09-00-000303","rule_title":"OL 9 must be configured so that the file integrity tool verifies Access Control Lists (ACLs).","fix_text":"Configure the file integrity tool to check file and directory ACLs. \n\nIf AIDE is installed, ensure the \"acl\" rule is present on all uncommented file and directory selection lists.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 is configured so that AIDE is verifying ACLs with the following command:\n\n$ sudo grep acl /etc/aide.conf \nAll= p+i+n+u+g+s+m+S+sha512+acl+xattrs+selinux\n\nIf the \"acl\" rule is not being used on all uncommented selection lines in the \"/etc/aide.conf\" file, or ACLs are not being checked by another file integrity tool, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"OL 9 installation media ships with an optional file integrity tool called Advanced Intrusion Detection Environment (AIDE). AIDE is highly configurable at install time. This requirement assumes the \"aide.conf\" file is under the \"/etc\" directory.\n\nACLs can provide permissions beyond those permitted through the file mode and must be verified by the file integrity tools.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"1088","uuid":"2573ade4-8981-4b59-b3d7-1b272b32ad66","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FCCC2198B95BB8AD20E51BBBB2C779439731F09D\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'OL 9 must be configured so that the file integrity tool verifies Access Control Lists (ACLs).' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271500","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271500","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271500","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-271500r1091212_rule","rule_id":"SV-271500","rule_version":"OL09-00-000304","rule_title":"OL 9 must be configured so that the file integrity tool verifies extended attributes.","fix_text":"Configure the file integrity tool to check file and directory extended attributes. \n\nIf AIDE is installed, ensure the \"xattrs\" rule is present on all uncommented file and directory selection lists.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 is configured so that AIDE is configured to verify extended attributes with the following command:\n\n$ sudo grep xattrs /etc/aide.conf \nAll= p+i+n+u+g+s+m+S+sha512+acl+xattrs+selinux\n\nIf the \"xattrs\" rule is not being used on all uncommented selection lines in the \"/etc/aide.conf\" file, or extended attributes are not being checked by another file integrity tool, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"OL 9 installation media ships with an optional file integrity tool called Advanced Intrusion Detection Environment (AIDE). AIDE is highly configurable at install time. This requirement assumes the \"aide.conf\" file is under the \"/etc\" directory.\n\nExtended attributes in file systems are used to contain arbitrary data and file metadata with security implications.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"2944","uuid":"31239367-4cf4-4537-8308-06571ae10b3c","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 852E6458467D31F38378F79DD6E9EA16C392457E\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'OL 9 must be configured so that the file integrity tool verifies extended attributes.' is not present or not in use on this the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271501","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271501","title":"SRG-OS-000355-GPOS-00143","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271501","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000355-GPOS-00143","rule_id_src":"SV-271501r1091215_rule","rule_id":"SV-271501","rule_version":"OL09-00-000310","rule_title":"OL 9 must have the chrony package installed.","fix_text":"Install the chrony package with the following command:\n \n$ sudo dnf install -y chrony","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 has the chrony package installed with the following command:\n\n$ dnf list --installed chrony\nInstalled Packages\nchrony.x86_64                                      4.5-1.0.2.el9                                      @ol9_baseos_latest        \n\nIf the chrony package is not installed, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inaccurate time stamps make it more difficult to correlate events and can lead to an inaccurate analysis. Determining the correct time a particular event occurred on a system is critical when conducting forensic analysis and investigating system events. Sources outside the configured acceptable allowance (drift) may be inaccurate.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-004923"],"reference_identifier":"1578","uuid":"7bd17da7-b002-4b85-a84d-c90a578acf6f","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A66C596682E438375D76660A332B43AB9BEAA196\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'OL 9 must have the chrony package installed.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271502","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271502","title":"SRG-OS-000355-GPOS-00143","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271502","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000355-GPOS-00143","rule_id_src":"SV-271502r1091218_rule","rule_id":"SV-271502","rule_version":"OL09-00-000311","rule_title":"OL 9 must enable the chronyd service.","fix_text":"Enable the chronyd service with the following command:\n\n$ sudo systemctl enable --now chronyd","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 chronyd service is set to active with the following command:\n\n$ systemctl is-active chronyd\nactive \n\nIf the chronyd service is not active, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inaccurate time stamps make it more difficult to correlate events and can lead to an inaccurate analysis. Determining the correct time a particular event occurred on a system is critical when conducting forensic analysis and investigating system events. Sources outside the configured acceptable allowance (drift) may be inaccurate.\n\nSynchronizing internal information system clocks provides uniformity of time stamps for information systems with multiple system clocks and systems connected over a network.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-004923"],"reference_identifier":"5646","uuid":"d2dc08b6-1296-4160-a059-1cd0f3c1a04e","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4287A6DC6A840CE0874FF5E74182BA1C6EE8BA83\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'OL 9 must enable the chronyd service.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271503","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271503","title":"SRG-OS-000378-GPOS-00163","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271503","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000378-GPOS-00163","rule_id_src":"SV-271503r1091221_rule","rule_id":"SV-271503","rule_version":"OL09-00-000320","rule_title":"OL 9 must have the USBGuard package installed.","fix_text":"Install the usbguard package with the following command:\n\n$ sudo dnf install -y usbguard","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 has USBGuard installed on the operating system with the following command:\n\n$ dnf list --installed usbguard\nInstalled Packages\nusbguard.x86_64                                       1.0.0-15.el9                                        @ol9_appstream\n\nIf the USBGuard package is not installed, ask the SA to indicate how unauthorized peripherals are being blocked.\n\nIf there is no evidence that unauthorized peripherals are being blocked before establishing a connection, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The USBguard-daemon is the main component of the USBGuard software framework. It runs as a service in the background and enforces the USB device authorization policy for all USB devices. The policy is defined by a set of rules using a rule language described in the usbguard-rules.conf file. The policy and the authorization state of USB devices can be modified during runtime using the usbguard tool.\n\nThe system administrator (SA) must work with the site information system security officer (ISSO) to determine a list of authorized peripherals and establish rules within the USBGuard software framework to allow only authorized devices.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001958"],"reference_identifier":"5430","uuid":"c1d08610-11af-4f0d-a556-f0eb6cbf72ec","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-271504","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271504","title":"SRG-OS-000378-GPOS-00163","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271504","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000378-GPOS-00163","rule_id_src":"SV-271504r1091224_rule","rule_id":"SV-271504","rule_version":"OL09-00-000321","rule_title":"OL 9 must enable the USBGuard package.","fix_text":"Enable the USBGuard service with the following command:\n\n$ sudo systemctl enable --now usbguard","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 USBGuard is enabled with the following command:\n\n$ systemctl is-active usbguard\nactive\n\nIf usbguard is not active, ask the SA to indicate how unauthorized peripherals are being blocked.\n\nIf there is no evidence that unauthorized peripherals are being blocked before establishing a connection, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The USBguard-daemon is the main component of the USBGuard software framework. It runs as a service in the background and enforces the USB device authorization policy for all USB devices. The policy is defined by a set of rules using a rule language described in the usbguard-rules.conf file. The policy and the authorization state of USB devices can be modified during runtime using the usbguard tool.\n\nThe system administrator (SA) must work with the site information system security officer (ISSO) to determine a list of authorized peripherals and establish rules within the USBGuard software framework to allow only authorized devices.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001958"],"reference_identifier":"1241","uuid":"c35a4d18-8476-4052-bcf0-04b21dbcde50","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 316D0A4A8942337A59FBF0EFD1517D2CAF6A912B\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'OL 9 must enable the USBGuard package.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271506","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271506","title":"SRG-OS-000370-GPOS-00155","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271506","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000370-GPOS-00155","rule_id_src":"SV-271506r1091230_rule","rule_id":"SV-271506","rule_version":"OL09-00-000340","rule_title":"OL 9 must have the fapolicy module installed.","fix_text":"Install the fapolicyd package with the following command:\n \n$ sudo dnf install -y fapolicyd","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 fapolicyd package is installed with the following command:\n\n$ dnf list --installed fapolicyd\nInstalled Packages\nfapolicyd.x86_64                                    1.3.2-100.0.1.el9                                     @ol9_appstream\n\nIf the fapolicyd package is not installed, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The organization must identify authorized software programs and permit execution of authorized software. The process used to identify software programs that are authorized to execute on organizational information systems is commonly referred to as allowlisting.\n\nUsing an allowlist provides a configuration management method for allowing the execution of only authorized software. Using only authorized software decreases risk by limiting the number of potential vulnerabilities. Verification of allowlisted software occurs prior to execution or at system startup.\n\nUser home directories/folders may contain information of a sensitive nature. Nonprivileged users should coordinate any sharing of information with a system administrator (SA) through shared resources.\n\nOL 9 ships with many optional packages. One such package is a file access policy daemon called \"fapolicyd\". \"fapolicyd\" is a userspace daemon that determines access rights to files based on attributes of the process and file. It can be used to either blocklist or allowlist processes or file access.\n\nProceed with caution with enforcing the use of this daemon. Improper configuration may render the system nonfunctional. The \"fapolicyd\" API is not namespace aware and can cause issues when launching or running containers.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000370-GPOS-00155, SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001774","CCI-001764"],"reference_identifier":"2505","uuid":"fcfd6137-59ba-4725-b80d-0d64a31a6158","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C4439B4AF355D901E4BCAF01BF8BA589870176C6\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'OL 9 must have the fapolicy module installed.' is not present or not in use on this the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271507","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271507","title":"SRG-OS-000370-GPOS-00155","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271507","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000370-GPOS-00155","rule_id_src":"SV-271507r1091233_rule","rule_id":"SV-271507","rule_version":"OL09-00-000341","rule_title":"OL 9 must enable the fapolicy module.","fix_text":"Enable the fapolicyd service with the following command:\n\n$ sudo systemctl enable --now fapolicyd","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 fapolicyd is active with the following command:\n\n$ systemctl is-active fapolicyd\nactive\n\nIf fapolicyd module is not active, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The organization must identify authorized software programs and permit execution of authorized software. The process used to identify software programs that are authorized to execute on organizational information systems is commonly referred to as allowlisting.\n\nUsing an allowlist provides a configuration management method for allowing the execution of only authorized software. Using only authorized software decreases risk by limiting the number of potential vulnerabilities. Verification of allowlisted software occurs prior to execution or at system startup.\n\nUser home directories/folders may contain information of a sensitive nature. Nonprivileged users should coordinate any sharing of information with a system administrator (SA) through shared resources.\n\nOL 9 ships with many optional packages. One such package is a file access policy daemon called \"fapolicyd\". \"fapolicyd\" is a userspace daemon that determines access rights to files based on attributes of the process and file. It can be used to either blocklist or allowlist processes or file access.\n\nProceed with caution with enforcing the use of this daemon. Improper configuration may render the system nonfunctional. The \"fapolicyd\" API is not namespace aware and can cause issues when launching or running containers.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000370-GPOS-00155, SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001774","CCI-001764"],"reference_identifier":"4067","uuid":"788cc67e-bf25-4573-b3fd-d5f5c629ed59","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: EBA074A9B3EFA1EE5ADFC5F0D2AC4041EA694281\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'OL 9 must enable the fapolicy module.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271508","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271508","title":"SRG-OS-000479-GPOS-00224","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271508","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000479-GPOS-00224","rule_id_src":"SV-271508r1091236_rule","rule_id":"SV-271508","rule_version":"OL09-00-000350","rule_title":"OL 9 must have the rsyslog package installed.","fix_text":"The rsyslogd package can be installed with the following command:\n \n$ sudo dnf install -y rsyslogd","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 has the rsyslogd package installed with the following command:\n\n$ dnf list --installed rsyslog\nInstalled Packages\nrsyslog.x86_64                                         8.2310.0-4.el9                                         @AppStream\n\nIf the rsyslogd package is not installed, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"rsyslogd is a system utility providing support for message logging. Support for both internet and Unix domain sockets enables this utility to support both local and remote logging. Couple this utility with \"gnutls\" (which is a secure communications library implementing the SSL, TLS, and DTLS protocols), to create a method to securely encrypt and offload auditing.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000479-GPOS-00224, SRG-OS-000051-GPOS-00024","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001851","CCI-000154"],"reference_identifier":"5691","uuid":"87b323ea-b8cd-412e-9386-9f6afba2790d","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: BC197B37E66C2A8FA484E23E011565DB47685F3A\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'OL 9 must have the rsyslog package installed.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271509","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271509","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271509","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-271509r1091239_rule","rule_id":"SV-271509","rule_version":"OL09-00-000351","rule_title":"OL 9 must be configured so that the rsyslog service is active.","fix_text":"Enable the rsyslog service with the following command:\n\n$ sudo systemctl enable --now rsyslog","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 rsyslog is active with the following command:\n\n$ systemctl is-active rsyslog \nactive\n\nIf the rsyslog service is not active, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The rsyslog service must be running to provide logging services, which are essential to system administration.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"9447","uuid":"c6d228f5-92a0-45da-bfa9-827baa8ad0d8","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 5CE83997BDE591BF1AE69C96C69EA3D4E3864BFA\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'OL 9 must be configured so that the rsyslog service is active.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271510","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271510","title":"SRG-OS-000120-GPOS-00061","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271510","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000120-GPOS-00061","rule_id_src":"SV-271510r1091242_rule","rule_id":"SV-271510","rule_version":"OL09-00-000355","rule_title":"OL 9 must have the packages required for encrypting offloaded audit logs installed.","fix_text":"Install the rsyslog-gnutls package with the following command:\n \n$ sudo dnf install -y rsyslog-gnutls","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 has the rsyslog-gnutls package installed with the following command:\n\n$ dnf list --installed rsyslog-gnutls\nInstalled Packages\nrsyslog-gnutls.x86_64                                     8.2310.0-4.el9                                      @AppStream\n\nIf the rsyslog-gnutls package is not installed, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The rsyslog-gnutls package provides Transport Layer Security (TLS) support for the rsyslog daemon, which enables secure remote logging.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000803"],"reference_identifier":"5963","uuid":"830bd2a1-7215-40ba-87cd-84bcf950261c","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 60D069E3416C937BF7A5B05C0906C7895901BC62\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'OL 9 must have the packages required for encrypting offloaded audit logs installed.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271511","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271511","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271511","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-271511r1091245_rule","rule_id":"SV-271511","rule_version":"OL09-00-000360","rule_title":"OL 9 must enable the hardware random number generator entropy gatherer service.","fix_text":"Install the rng-tools package with the following command:\n\n$ sudo dnf install -y rng-tools\n\nEnable the rngd service run the following command:\n\n$ sudo systemctl enable --now rngd","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 has enabled the hardware random number generator entropy gatherer service with the following command:\n\n$ systemctl is-active rngd\nactive\n\nIf the rngd service is not active, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The most important characteristic of a random number generator is its randomness, namely its ability to deliver random numbers that are impossible to predict. Entropy in computer security is associated with the unpredictability of a source of randomness. The random source with high entropy tends to achieve a uniform distribution of random values. Random number generators are one of the most important building blocks of cryptosystems.\n\nThe rngd service feeds random data from hardware device to kernel random device. Quality (nonpredictable) random number generation is important for several security functions (i.e., ciphers).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4955","uuid":"739bd248-b022-440e-a72c-29e8e5f3ae3e","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A987921D624BD111D157D84C7953DFCAA20E7B4E\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'OL 9 must enable the hardware random number generator entropy gatherer service.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271512","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271512","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271512","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-271512r1091248_rule","rule_id":"SV-271512","rule_version":"OL09-00-000370","rule_title":"OL 9 must have the rng-tools package installed.","fix_text":"Install the rng-tools package with the following command:\n \n$ sudo dnf install -y rng-tools","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 has the rng-tools package installed with the following command:\n\n$ dnf list --installed rng-tools\nInstalled Packages\nrng-tools.x86_64                                      6.16-1.el9                                      @ol9_baseos_latest\n\nIf the rng-tools package is not installed, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"rng-tools provides hardware random number generator tools, such as those used in the formation of x509/PKI certificates.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5995","uuid":"36457a29-eeb2-43ce-b9ba-719ad19e2e11","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A703452D4632EC6980FDEC0C7C9574652B04B89D\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'OL 9 must have the rng-tools package installed.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271513","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271513","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271513","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-271513r1091251_rule","rule_id":"SV-271513","rule_version":"OL09-00-000380","rule_title":"OL 9 must have the nss-tools package installed.","fix_text":"Install the nss-tools package with the following command:\n \n$ sudo dnf install -y nss-tools","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 has the nss-tools package installed with the following command:\n\n$ dnf list --installed nss-tools\nInstalled Packages\nnss-tools.x86_64                                     3.101.0-7.el9_2                                      @ol9_appstream\n\nIf the nss-tools package is not installed, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Network Security Services (NSS) is a set of libraries designed to support cross-platform development of security-enabled client and server applications. Install the \"nss-tools\" package to install command-line tools to manipulate the NSS certificate and key database.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"9843","uuid":"26cd7f1a-ebb9-4788-ad40-c002d730e0f8","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1166BDC92D30A3965D93648032CD20CC55A602EE\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'OL 9 must have the nss-tools package installed.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271514","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271514","title":"SRG-OS-000375-GPOS-00160","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271514","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000375-GPOS-00160","rule_id_src":"SV-271514r1091254_rule","rule_id":"SV-271514","rule_version":"OL09-00-000390","rule_title":"OL 9 must have the pcsc-lite package installed.","fix_text":"Install the pcsc-lite package with the following command:\n \n$ sudo dnf install -y pcsc-lite","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 has the pcsc-lite package installed with the following command:\n\n$ dnf list --installed pcsc-lite\nInstalled Packages\npcsc-lite.x86_64                                     1.9.4-1.el9                                      @ol9_baseos_latest\n\nIf the pcsc-lite package is not installed, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The pcsc-lite package must be installed if it is to be available for multifactor authentication using smart cards.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-004046"],"reference_identifier":"7210","uuid":"1aacd2a1-8f75-49ad-a143-a308fc8ca6b2","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F63422AF6EBC05B16DE39AD8449117540C5EDC69\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'OL 9 must have the pcsc-lite package installed.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271515","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271515","title":"SRG-OS-000375-GPOS-00160","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271515","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000375-GPOS-00160","rule_id_src":"SV-271515r1091257_rule","rule_id":"SV-271515","rule_version":"OL09-00-000400","rule_title":"OL 9 must have the opensc package installed.","fix_text":"Install the opensc package with the following command:\n \n$ sudo dnf install -y opensc","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 has the opensc package installed with the following command:\n\n$ dnf list --installed opensc\nInstalled Packages\nopensc.x86_64                                     0.23.0-4.el9_3                                      @ol9_baseos_latest\n\nIf the opensc package is not installed, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The use of PIV credentials facilitates standardization and reduces the risk of unauthorized access.\n\nThe DOD has mandated the use of the Common Access Card (CAC) to support identity management and personal authentication for systems covered under Homeland Security Presidential Directive (HSPD) 12, as well as making the CAC a primary component of layered protection for national security systems.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000375-GPOS-00160, SRG-OS-000376-GPOS-00161","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-004046","CCI-001953"],"reference_identifier":"8134","uuid":"b7ceda27-a8c7-4816-a827-6ced11c2c947","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 30ECDA9B297EF0B829C08837C9CA1A6A7176652A\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'OL 9 must have the opensc package installed.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271516","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271516","title":"SRG-OS-000375-GPOS-00160","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271516","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000375-GPOS-00160","rule_id_src":"SV-271516r1091260_rule","rule_id":"SV-271516","rule_version":"OL09-00-000401","rule_title":"OL 9 must be configured so that the pcscd service is active.","fix_text":"Enable the pcscd service with the following command:\n\n$ sudo systemctl enable --now pcscd","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 pcscd service is active with the following command:\n\n$ systemctl is-active pcscd\nactive\n\nIf the pcscdservice is not active, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The information system ensures that even if the information system is compromised, that compromise will not affect credentials stored on the authentication device.\n\nThe daemon program for pcsc-lite and the MuscleCard framework is pcscd. It is a resource manager that coordinates communications with smart card readers and smart cards and cryptographic tokens that are connected to the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-004046"],"reference_identifier":"1772","uuid":"373a898e-8796-4ec0-a3ce-915bd1bff8ac","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 3EBE0565E667B9C78E4337C7D8C5E26C6C43DE5C\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'OL 9 must be configured so that the pcscd service is active.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271517","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271517","title":"SRG-OS-000120-GPOS-00061","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271517","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000120-GPOS-00061","rule_id_src":"SV-271517r1101885_rule","rule_id":"SV-271517","rule_version":"OL09-00-000410","rule_title":"OL 9 must have the libreswan package installed.","fix_text":"Install the libreswan service (if it is not already installed) with the following command:\n\n$ sudo dnf install -y libreswan","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Note: If there is no operational need for Libreswan to be installed, this rule is not applicable.\n\nVerify that OL 9 libreswan service package is installed.\n\nCheck that the libreswan service package is installed with the following command:\n\n$ dnf list --installed libreswan\nInstalled Packages\nlibreswan.x86_64                                    4.12-2.0.1.el9_4.1                                    @ol9_appstream\n\nIf the libreswan package is not installed, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Providing the ability for remote users or systems to initiate a secure VPN connection protects information when it is transmitted over a wide area network.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000803"],"reference_identifier":"4230","uuid":"873a77e3-b0eb-43c2-83cb-4902f540450b","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7C81DF35ED818AC6768F1D01BA9700D64923DFD1\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'OL 9 must have the libreswan package installed.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271518","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271518","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271518","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-271518r1091266_rule","rule_id":"SV-271518","rule_version":"OL09-00-000430","rule_title":"OL 9 must have the gnutls-utils package installed.","fix_text":"Install the gnutls-utils package with the following command:\n \n$ sudo dnf install -y gnutls-utils","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 has the gnutls-utils package installed with the following command:\n\n$ dnf list --installed gnutls-utils\nInstalled Packages\ngnutls-utils.x86_64                                     3.8.3-4.el9_4                                     @ol9_appstream\n\nIf the gnutls-utils package is not installed, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"GnuTLS is a secure communications library implementing the SSL, TLS, and DTLS protocols and technologies around them. It provides a simple C language application programming interface (API) to access the secure communications protocols as well as APIs to parse and write X.509, PKCS #12, OpenPGP and other required structures. This package contains command line TLS client and server and certificate manipulation tools.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"1479","uuid":"4090fbd0-3921-435e-a6b9-954c2ffdc417","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C5D58861BC95EC3D3A90C92099F11A4985677830\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'OL 9 must have the gnutls-utils package installed.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271519","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271519","title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271519","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","rule_id_src":"SV-271519r1091269_rule","rule_id":"SV-271519","rule_version":"OL09-00-000440","rule_title":"OL 9 must have the audit package installed.","fix_text":"Install the audit service package (if the audit service is not already installed) with the following command:\n\n$ sudo dnf install -y audit","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 audit service package is installed.\n\nCheck that the audit service package is installed with the following command:\n\n$ dnf list --installed audit\nInstalled Packages\naudit.x86_64                                     3.1.2-2.0.1.el9                                      @ol9_baseos_latest\n\nIf the audit package is not installed, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Without establishing what type of events occurred, the source of events, where events occurred, and the outcome of events, it would be difficult to establish, correlate, and investigate the events leading up to an outage or attack.\n\nAudit record content that may be necessary to satisfy this requirement includes, for example, time stamps, source and destination addresses, user/process identifiers, event descriptions, success/fail indications, filenames involved, and access control or flow control rules invoked.\n\nAssociating event types with detected events in audit logs provides a means of investigating an attack, recognizing resource utilization or capacity thresholds, or identifying an improperly configured OL 9 system.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031, SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015, SRG-OS-000038-GPOS-00016, SRG-OS-000039-GPOS-00017, SRG-OS-000040-GPOS-00018, SRG-OS-000041-GPOS-00019, SRG-OS-000042-GPOS-00021, SRG-OS-000051-GPOS-00024, SRG-OS-000054-GPOS-00025, SRG-OS-000122-GPOS-00063, SRG-OS-000254-GPOS-00095, SRG-OS-000255-GPOS-00096, SRG-OS-000337-GPOS-00129, SRG-OS-000348-GPOS-00136, SRG-OS-000349-GPOS-00137, SRG-OS-000350-GPOS-00138, SRG-OS-000351-GPOS-00139, SRG-OS-000352-GPOS-00140, SRG-OS-000353-GPOS-00141, SRG-OS-000354-GPOS-00142, SRG-OS-000358-GPOS-00145, SRG-OS-000365-GPOS-00152, SRG-OS-000392-GPOS-00172, SRG-OS-000475-GPOS-00220, SRG-OS-000055-GPOS-00026","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000169","CCI-000130","CCI-000131","CCI-000132","CCI-000133","CCI-000134","CCI-000135","CCI-000154","CCI-000158","CCI-001876","CCI-001464","CCI-001487","CCI-001914","CCI-001875","CCI-001877","CCI-001878","CCI-001879","CCI-001880","CCI-001881","CCI-001882","CCI-001889","CCI-003938","CCI-002884","CCI-000172","CCI-000159"],"reference_identifier":"3817","uuid":"71e7226e-9636-4d75-9678-df077f13d979","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1AB383D72AB61087C536B247DDC5FD775DA7EB1E\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'OL 9 must have the audit package installed.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271520","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271520","title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271520","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","rule_id_src":"SV-271520r1091272_rule","rule_id":"SV-271520","rule_version":"OL09-00-000441","rule_title":"OL 9 audit service must be enabled.","fix_text":"Enable the auditd service with the following command:\n\n$ sudo systemctl enable --now auditd","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 audit service is configured to produce audit records with the following command:\n\n$ systemctl status auditd.service\nauditd.service - Security Auditing Service\nLoaded:loaded (/usr/lib/systemd/system/auditd.service; enabled; vendor preset: enabled)\nActive: active (running) since Tues 2022-05-24 12:56:56 EST; 4 weeks 0 days ago\n\nIf the audit service is not \"active\" and \"running\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Without establishing what type of events occurred, it would be difficult to establish, correlate, and investigate the events leading up to an outage or attack. Ensuring the \"auditd\" service is active ensures audit records generated by the kernel are appropriately recorded.\n\nAdditionally, a properly configured audit subsystem ensures that actions of individual system users can be uniquely traced to those users so they can be held accountable for their actions.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031, SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015, SRG-OS-000038-GPOS-00016, SRG-OS-000039-GPOS-00017, SRG-OS-000040-GPOS-00018, SRG-OS-000041-GPOS-00019, SRG-OS-000042-GPOS-00021, SRG-OS-000051-GPOS-00024, SRG-OS-000054-GPOS-00025, SRG-OS-000122-GPOS-00063, SRG-OS-000254-GPOS-00095, SRG-OS-000255-GPOS-00096, SRG-OS-000337-GPOS-00129, SRG-OS-000348-GPOS-00136, SRG-OS-000349-GPOS-00137, SRG-OS-000350-GPOS-00138, SRG-OS-000351-GPOS-00139, SRG-OS-000352-GPOS-00140, SRG-OS-000353-GPOS-00141, SRG-OS-000354-GPOS-00142, SRG-OS-000358-GPOS-00145, SRG-OS-000365-GPOS-00152, SRG-OS-000392-GPOS-00172, SRG-OS-000475-GPOS-00220","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000169","CCI-000130","CCI-000131","CCI-000132","CCI-000133","CCI-000134","CCI-000135","CCI-000154","CCI-000158","CCI-001876","CCI-001464","CCI-001487","CCI-001914","CCI-001875","CCI-001877","CCI-001878","CCI-001879","CCI-001880","CCI-001881","CCI-001882","CCI-001889","CCI-003938","CCI-002884","CCI-000172"],"reference_identifier":"3860","uuid":"c7169884-5e46-4460-848a-cb2a60e56ee7","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4096A8AB013429CE1D7864477C0E9DFF74FEE3E0\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'OL 9 audit service must be enabled.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271521","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271521","title":"SRG-OS-000342-GPOS-00133","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271521","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000342-GPOS-00133","rule_id_src":"SV-271521r1091275_rule","rule_id":"SV-271521","rule_version":"OL09-00-000450","rule_title":"OL 9 must have the audispd-plugins package installed.","fix_text":"The audispd-plugins package can be installed with the following command:\n \n$ sudo dnf install -y audispd-plugins","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 has the audispd-plugins package for installed with the following command:\n\n$ dnf list --installed audispd-plugins\n\nExample output:\nInstalled Packages\naudispd-plugins.x86_64                                3.1.2-2.0.1.el9                                 @ol9_baseos_latest\n\nIf the audispd-plugins package is not installed, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"audispd-plugins provides plug-ins for the real-time interface to the audit subsystem, audispd. These plug-ins can do things like relay events to remote machines or analyze events for suspicious behavior.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001851"],"reference_identifier":"3839","uuid":"9a5ade06-cd21-4888-ac5d-96e7e04249e4","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4AFAE5D1D57F59D244742B01DF5477E56D18ABF6\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'OL 9 must have the audispd-plugins package installed.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271522","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271522","title":"SRG-OS-000437-GPOS-00194","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271522","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000437-GPOS-00194","rule_id_src":"SV-271522r1091278_rule","rule_id":"SV-271522","rule_version":"OL09-00-000495","rule_title":"OL 9 must remove all software components after updated versions have been installed.","fix_text":"Configure OL 9 to remove all software components after updated versions have been installed.\n\nEdit the file /etc/dnf/dnf.conf by adding or editing the following line:\n\n clean_requirements_on_remove=1","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 removes all software components after updated versions have been installed with the following command:\n\n$ grep clean /etc/dnf/dnf.conf \nclean_requirements_on_remove=True \n\nIf clean_requirements_on_remove is not set to \"True\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Previous versions of software components that are not removed from the information system after updates have been installed may be exploited by some adversaries.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002617"],"reference_identifier":"8308","uuid":"aaad1739-6d8c-4e2b-8389-7d93a5f72a0a","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E3E10381080791CA45E509BC1A147CA2F31BFE42\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'OL 9 must remove all software components after updated versions have been installed.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271523","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271523","title":"SRG-OS-000366-GPOS-00153","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271523","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000366-GPOS-00153","rule_id_src":"SV-271523r1091281_rule","rule_id":"SV-271523","rule_version":"OL09-00-000496","rule_title":"OL 9 must check the GPG signature of locally installed software packages before installation.","fix_text":"Configure dnf to always check the GPG signature of local software packages before installation.\n\nAdd or update the following line in the [main] section of the /etc/dnf/dnf.conf file:\n\nlocalpkg_gpgcheck=1","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 dnf package manager always checks the GPG signature of locally installed software packages before installation:\n\n$ grep localpkg_gpgcheck /etc/dnf/dnf.conf \nlocalpkg_gpgcheck=1 \n\nIf \"localpkg_gpgcheck\" is not set to \"1\", or if the option is missing or commented out, ask the system administrator how the GPG signatures of local software packages are being verified.\n\nIf there is no process to verify GPG signatures that is approved by the organization, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Changes to any software components can have significant effects on the overall security of the operating system. This requirement ensures the software has not been tampered with and that it has been provided by a trusted vendor.\n\nAll software packages must be signed with a cryptographic key recognized and approved by the organization.\n\nVerifying the authenticity of software prior to installation validates the integrity of the software package received from a vendor. This verifies the software has not been tampered with and that it has been provided by a trusted vendor.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-003992"],"reference_identifier":"4993","uuid":"e5d3ce6e-b6f4-4386-92ce-052070a6222d","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 5F085E70EB3E0464CE0CC714D9FF5CCD7A4B2D60\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'OL 9 must check the GPG signature of locally installed software packages before installation.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271524","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271524","title":"SRG-OS-000366-GPOS-00153","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271524","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000366-GPOS-00153","rule_id_src":"SV-271524r1091284_rule","rule_id":"SV-271524","rule_version":"OL09-00-000497","rule_title":"OL 9 must check the GPG signature of software packages originating from external software repositories before installation.","fix_text":"Configure dnf to always check the GPG signature of software packages originating from external software repositories before installation.\n\nAdd or update the following line in the [main] section of the /etc/dnf/dnf.conf file:\n\ngpgcheck=1","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 dnf package manager always checks the GPG signature of software packages originating from external software repositories before installation:\n\n$ grep gpgcheck /etc/dnf/dnf.conf\ngpgcheck=1\n\nIf \"gpgcheck\" is not set to \"1\", or if the option is missing or commented out, ask the system administrator how the GPG signatures of software packages are being verified.\n\nIf there is no process to verify GPG signatures that is approved by the organization, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Changes to any software components can have significant effects on the overall security of the operating system. This requirement ensures the software has not been tampered with and that it has been provided by a trusted vendor.\n\nAll software packages must be signed with a cryptographic key recognized and approved by the organization.\n\nVerifying the authenticity of software prior to installation validates the integrity of the software package received from a vendor. This verifies the software has not been tampered with and that it has been provided by a trusted vendor.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-003992"],"reference_identifier":"8083","uuid":"c36af8ea-7f96-40c6-8432-1f505b8d5eaf","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 37AC6A904217F056B1F1BCA80FB61D03CFEEAB18\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'OL 9 must check the GPG signature of software packages originating from external software repositories before installation.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271525","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271525","title":"SRG-OS-000366-GPOS-00153","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271525","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000366-GPOS-00153","rule_id_src":"SV-271525r1091287_rule","rule_id":"SV-271525","rule_version":"OL09-00-000498","rule_title":"OL 9 must have GPG signature verification enabled for all software repositories.","fix_text":"Configure all software repositories defined in \"/etc/yum.repos.d/\" to have \"gpgcheck\" enabled:\n\n$ sudo sed -i 's/gpgcheck\\s*=.*/gpgcheck=1/g' /etc/yum.repos.d/*","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 software repositories defined in \"/etc/yum.repos.d/\" have been configured with \"gpgcheck\" enabled:\n\n$ grep gpgcheck /etc/yum.repos.d/*.repo | more\ngpgcheck = 1\n\nIf \"gpgcheck\" is not set to \"1\" for all returned lines, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Changes to any software components can have significant effects on the overall security of the operating system. This requirement ensures the software has not been tampered with and that it has been provided by a trusted vendor.\n\nAll software packages must be signed with a cryptographic key recognized and approved by the organization.\n\nVerifying the authenticity of software prior to installation validates the integrity of the software package received from a vendor. This verifies the software has not been tampered with and that it has been provided by a trusted vendor.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-003992"],"reference_identifier":"5133","uuid":"beb1af59-429c-4fdb-8a71-8cfa7f5ea558","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D7506B523AD0D4664EB0B3C3184C8F0DD4739D97\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'OL 9 must have GPG signature verification enabled for all software repositories.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271526","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271526","title":"SRG-OS-000366-GPOS-00153","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271526","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000366-GPOS-00153","rule_id_src":"SV-271526r1092460_rule","rule_id":"SV-271526","rule_version":"OL09-00-000499","rule_title":"OL 9 must ensure cryptographic verification of vendor software packages.","fix_text":"Install Oracle package-signing keys on the system and verify their fingerprints match vendor values.\n\nTo verify Oracle Linux Downloads, users need:\n-A checksum file corresponding to the downloaded ISO.\n-The public GPG key to verify the Oracle key used to sign the checksum file.\n\nThe checksum file contains a list of files that are part of a download package with the corresponding checksums as well as a GPG signature. The GPG signature enables anyone to verify that checksum file was published by Oracle. The steps below describe how to verify they checksum file itself and then verify the contents of the Oracle Linux download by checking against the checksum file.\n\nImport the Oracle Linux GPG key corresponding to the Oracle Linux release:\n\n$ curl https://yum.oracle.com/RPM-GPG-KEY-oracle-ol9 | gpg --import\n\nNote: No \"sudo\" for curl command\n\nDownload the appropriate checksum file and place it in the same directory as the Oracle Linux ISO download:\n\n$ curl https://linux.oracle.com/security/gpg/checksum/OracleLinux-R9-U3-Server-x86_64.checksum > OracleLinux-R9-U3-Server-x86_64.checksum\n\nDownload GPG Key:\n\n $ curl https://yum.oracle.com/RPM-GPG-KEY-oracle-ol9 -o RPM-GPG-KEY-oracle\nNote: No \"sudo\" for curl command\n\nTo verify the checksum file:\n\n$ gpg --verify-files OracleLinux-R9-U3-Server-x86_64.checksum\ngpg: Signature made Wed 15 Nov 2023 07:22:32 AM EST\ngpg:                using RSA key 3E6D826D3FBAB389C2F38E34BC4D06A08D8B756F\ngpg:                issuer \"secalert_us@oracle.com\"\ngpg: Good signature from \"Oracle Linux (release key 1) <secalert_us@oracle.com>\" [unknown]\ngpg: WARNING: The key's User ID is not certified with a trusted signature!\ngpg:          There is no indication that the signature belongs to the owner.\nPrimary key fingerprint: 3E6D 826D 3FBA B389 C2F3  8E34 BC4D 06A0 8D8B 756F\n\nVerify the ISO download as follows:\n\n$ grep OracleLinux-R9-U3-x86_64-boot.iso OracleLinux-R9-U3-Server-x86_64.checksum | sha256sum -c\n\nOracleLinux-R9-U3-x86_64-boot.iso: OK","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 ensures cryptographic verification of vendor software packages by confirming that Oracle package-signing keys are installed on the system, and verify their fingerprints match vendor values.\n\nNote: For OL 9 software packages, Oracle uses GPG keys labeled \"release key 1\" and \"auxiliary key 1\". The keys are defined in key file \"/etc/pki/rpm-gpg/RPM-GPG-KEY-oracle\" by default.\n\nList Oracle GPG keys installed on the system:\n\n$ sudo rpm -q --queryformat \"%{SUMMARY}\\n\" gpg-pubkey | grep -i \"oracle\"\n\nOracle Linux (release key 1) <secalert_us@oracle.com> public key\nOracle Linux (backup key 1) <secalert_us@oracle.com> public key\n\nIf Oracle GPG keys \"release key 1\" and \"backup key 1\" are not installed, this is a finding.\n\nList key fingerprints of installed Oracle GPG keys:\n\n$ sudo gpg -q --keyid-format short --with-fingerprint /etc/pki/rpm-gpg/RPM-GPG-KEY-oracle\n\nIf key file \"/etc/pki/rpm-gpg/RPM-GPG-KEY-oracle\" is missing, this is a finding.\n\npub   rsa4096/8D8B756F 2022-01-19 [SC] [expires: 2042-01-14]\n      Key fingerprint = 3E6D 826D 3FBA B389 C2F3  8E34 BC4D 06A0 8D8B 756F\nuid                   Oracle Linux (release key 1) <secalert_us@oracle.com>\nsub   rsa4096/2E708C25 2022-01-19 [E] [expires: 2041-06-01]\npub   rsa4096/8B4EFBE6 2022-01-19 [SC] [expires: 2042-01-14]\n      Key fingerprint = 9822 3175 9C74 6706 5D0C  E9B2 A7DD 0708 8B4E FBE6\nuid                   Oracle Linux (backup key 1) <secalert_us@oracle.com>\nsub   rsa4096/DA900791 2022-01-19 [E] [expires: 2041-06-02]\n\nCompare key fingerprints of installed Oracle GPG keys with fingerprints listed for OL 9 on Oracle verification webpage at https://linux.oracle.com/security/gpg/#gpg.\n\nIf key fingerprints do not match, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Cryptographic verification of vendor software packages ensures that all software packages are obtained from a valid source and protects against spoofing that could lead to installation of malware on the system. Oracle cryptographically signs all software packages, which includes updates, with a GPG key to verify that they are valid.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-003992"],"reference_identifier":"9133","uuid":"eb237842-c6d9-444d-bdd0-27e750f37d54","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 979289EBB66071708C026D1668702BCA03A44005\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'OL 9 must ensure cryptographic verification of vendor software packages.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271527","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271527","title":"SRG-OS-000004-GPOS-00004","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271527","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000004-GPOS-00004","rule_id_src":"SV-271527r1092474_rule","rule_id":"SV-271527","rule_version":"OL09-00-000500","rule_title":"OL 9 must generate audit records for all account creations, modifications, disabling, and termination events that affect /etc/sudoers.","fix_text":"Configure OL 9 to generate audit records for all account creations, modifications, disabling, and termination events that affect \"/etc/sudoers\".\n\nAdd or update the following file system rule to \"/etc/audit/rules.d/audit.rules\":\n\n-w /etc/sudoers -p wa -k identity\n\nThe audit daemon must be restarted for the changes to take effect.\n\nRestart auditd:\n$ sudo service auditd restart","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 generates audit records for all account creations, modifications, disabling, and termination events that affect \"/etc/sudoers\" with the following command:\n\n$ sudo auditctl -l | grep /etc/sudoers\n-w /etc/sudoers -p wa -k identity\n-w /etc/sudoers.d -p wa -k identity\n\nIf the command does not return a line or the line is commented out, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The actions taken by system administrators must be audited to keep a record of what was executed on the system, as well as for accountability purposes. Editing the sudoers file may be sign of an attacker trying to establish persistent methods to a system, auditing the editing of the sudoers files mitigates this risk.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000004-GPOS-00004, SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015, SRG-OS-000042-GPOS-00020, SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031, SRG-OS-000304-GPOS-00121, SRG-OS-000392-GPOS-00172, SRG-OS-000462-GPOS-00206, SRG-OS-000470-GPOS-00214, SRG-OS-000471-GPOS-00215, SRG-OS-000239-GPOS-00089, SRG-OS-000240-GPOS-00090, SRG-OS-000241-GPOS-00091, SRG-OS-000303-GPOS-00120, SRG-OS-000466-GPOS-00210, SRG-OS-000476-GPOS-00221","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000018","CCI-000130","CCI-000135","CCI-000169","CCI-000015","CCI-002884","CCI-000172","CCI-001403","CCI-001404","CCI-001405","CCI-002130"],"reference_identifier":"9294","uuid":"3b5f71e9-2ecc-4a2f-9082-4255a71d386a","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 258EB48961B7E49183D4604113C8960B83EA8EFA\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'OL 9 must generate audit records for all account creations, modifications, disabling, and termination events that affect /etc/sudoers.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271528","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271528","title":"SRG-OS-000004-GPOS-00004","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271528","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000004-GPOS-00004","rule_id_src":"SV-271528r1092476_rule","rule_id":"SV-271528","rule_version":"OL09-00-000505","rule_title":"OL 9 must generate audit records for all account creations, modifications, disabling, and termination events that affect /etc/sudoers.d/ directory.","fix_text":"Configure OL 9 to generate audit records for all account creations, modifications, disabling, and termination events that affect \"/etc/sudoers.d/\".\n\nAdd or update the following file system rule to \"/etc/audit/rules.d/audit.rules\":\n\n-w /etc/sudoers.d/ -p wa -k identity\n\nThe audit daemon must be restarted for the changes to take effect.\n\nRestart auditd:\n$ sudo service auditd restart","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 generates audit records for all account creations, modifications, disabling, and termination events that affect \"/etc/sudoers.d/\" with the following command:\n\n$ sudo auditctl -l | grep /etc/sudoers.d\n-w /etc/sudoers.d/ -p wa -k identity\n\nIf the command does not return a line or the line is commented out, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The actions taken by system administrators must be audited to keep a record of what was executed on the system, as well as for accountability purposes. Editing the sudoers file may be sign of an attacker trying to establish persistent methods to a system, auditing the editing of the sudoers files mitigates this risk.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000004-GPOS-00004, SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015, SRG-OS-000042-GPOS-00020, SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031, SRG-OS-000304-GPOS-00121, SRG-OS-000392-GPOS-00172, SRG-OS-000462-GPOS-00206, SRG-OS-000470-GPOS-00214, SRG-OS-000471-GPOS-00215, SRG-OS-000239-GPOS-00089, SRG-OS-000240-GPOS-00090, SRG-OS-000241-GPOS-00091, SRG-OS-000303-GPOS-00120, SRG-OS-000466-GPOS-00210, SRG-OS-000476-GPOS-00221","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000018","CCI-000130","CCI-000135","CCI-000169","CCI-000015","CCI-002884","CCI-000172","CCI-001403","CCI-001404","CCI-001405","CCI-002130"],"reference_identifier":"5567","uuid":"0e940198-4998-4a56-88cb-85fc8e402a0a","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1EBD0E30729D3C90040B58E16967D37C00F0C030\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'OL 9 must generate audit records for all account creations, modifications, disabling, and termination events that affect /etc/sudoers.d/ directory.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271529","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271529","title":"SRG-OS-000004-GPOS-00004","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271529","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000004-GPOS-00004","rule_id_src":"SV-271529r1092478_rule","rule_id":"SV-271529","rule_version":"OL09-00-000510","rule_title":"OL 9 must generate audit records for all account creations, modifications, disabling, and termination events that affect /etc/group.","fix_text":"Configure OL 9 to generate audit records for all account creations, modifications, disabling, and termination events that affect \"/etc/group\".\n\nAdd or update the following file system rule to \"/etc/audit/rules.d/audit.rules\":\n\n-w /etc/group -p wa -k identity\n\nThe audit daemon must be restarted for the changes to take effect.\n\nRestart auditd:\n$ sudo service auditd restart","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 generates audit records for all account creations, modifications, disabling, and termination events that affect \"/etc/group\" with the following command:\n\n$ sudo auditctl -l | egrep '(/etc/group)'  \n-w /etc/group -p wa -k identity\n\nIf the command does not return a line or the line is commented out, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"In addition to auditing new user and group accounts, these watches will alert the system administrator(s) to any modifications. Any unexpected users, groups, or modifications must be investigated for legitimacy.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000004-GPOS-00004, SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015, SRG-OS-000042-GPOS-00020, SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031, SRG-OS-000304-GPOS-00121, SRG-OS-000392-GPOS-00172, SRG-OS-000462-GPOS-00206, SRG-OS-000470-GPOS-00214, SRG-OS-000471-GPOS-00215, SRG-OS-000239-GPOS-00089, SRG-OS-000240-GPOS-00090, SRG-OS-000241-GPOS-00091, SRG-OS-000303-GPOS-00120, SRG-OS-000466-GPOS-00210, SRG-OS-000476-GPOS-00221","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000018","CCI-000130","CCI-000135","CCI-000169","CCI-000015","CCI-002884","CCI-000172","CCI-001403","CCI-001404","CCI-001405","CCI-002130"],"reference_identifier":"8529","uuid":"383cc679-4455-48f2-9b6c-2d628b885137","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: B2E6E3C6671E510E813E6FFB496E1B5D2A7EB7CE\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'OL 9 must generate audit records for all account creations, modifications, disabling, and termination events that affect /etc/group.' is not present or not in use on this the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271530","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271530","title":"SRG-OS-000004-GPOS-00004","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271530","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000004-GPOS-00004","rule_id_src":"SV-271530r1092480_rule","rule_id":"SV-271530","rule_version":"OL09-00-000515","rule_title":"OL 9 must generate audit records for all account creations, modifications, disabling, and termination events that affect /etc/gshadow.","fix_text":"Configure OL 9 to generate audit records for all account creations, modifications, disabling, and termination events that affect \"/etc/gshadow\".\n\nAdd or update the following file system rule to \"/etc/audit/rules.d/audit.rules\":\n\n-w /etc/gshadow -p wa -k identity\n\nThe audit daemon must be restarted for the changes to take effect.\n\nRestart auditd:\n$ sudo service auditd restart","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 generates audit records for all account creations, modifications, disabling, and termination events that affect \"/etc/gshadow\" with the following command:\n\n$ sudo auditctl -l | egrep '(/etc/gshadow)' \n-w /etc/gshadow -p wa -k identity\n\nIf the command does not return a line or the line is commented out, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"In addition to auditing new user and group accounts, these watches will alert the system administrator(s) to any modifications. Any unexpected users, groups, or modifications should be investigated for legitimacy.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000004-GPOS-00004, SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015, SRG-OS-000042-GPOS-00020, SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031, SRG-OS-000304-GPOS-00121, SRG-OS-000392-GPOS-00172, SRG-OS-000462-GPOS-00206, SRG-OS-000470-GPOS-00214, SRG-OS-000471-GPOS-00215, SRG-OS-000239-GPOS-00089, SRG-OS-000240-GPOS-00090, SRG-OS-000241-GPOS-00091, SRG-OS-000303-GPOS-00120, SRG-OS-000466-GPOS-00210, SRG-OS-000476-GPOS-00221","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000018","CCI-000130","CCI-000135","CCI-000169","CCI-000015","CCI-002884","CCI-000172","CCI-001403","CCI-001404","CCI-001405","CCI-002130"],"reference_identifier":"6795","uuid":"ab160f10-02c3-4dc7-9a47-b9f801016e4e","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A22CF7321C15A8E5E60430E4D822BDBF131405A8\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'OL 9 must generate audit records for all account creations, modifications, disabling, and termination events that affect /etc/gshadow.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271531","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271531","title":"SRG-OS-000004-GPOS-00