1791","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000259-GPOS-00100","rule_id_src":"SV-271791r1134971_rule","rule_id":"SV-271791","rule_version":"OL09-00-002525","rule_title":"OL 9 library files must have mode 0755 or less permissive.","fix_text":"Configure the systemwide shared library files contained in the directories \"/lib\", \"/lib64\", \"/usr/lib\", and \"/usr/lib64\" to have mode 0755 or less permissive with the following command:\n\n$ sudo find /lib /lib64 /usr/lib /usr/lib64 -type f -name '*.so*' -perm /022 -exec chmod go-w {} +","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 systemwide shared library files contained in the directories \"/lib\", \"/lib64\", \"/usr/lib\", and \"/usr/lib64\" have mode 0755 or less permissive.\n\nCheck that the systemwide shared library files have mode 0755 or less permissive with the following command:\n\n$ sudo find /lib /lib64 /usr/lib /usr/lib64 -type f -name '*.so*' -perm /022 -exec stat -c \"%n %a\" {} +\n\nIf any output is returned, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If OL 9 allowed any user to make changes to software libraries, then those changes might be implemented without undergoing the appropriate testing and approvals that are part of a robust change management process.\n\nThis requirement applies to OL 9 with software libraries that are accessible and configurable, as in the case of interpreted languages. Software libraries also include privileged programs that execute with escalated privileges.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001499"],"reference_identifier":"2538","uuid":"b3ce4179-11d0-44ca-afbe-0339a01fc623","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 3A448453E19561343FB00B899C089265EDB8D911\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'OL 9 library files must have mode 0755 or less permissive.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271792","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271792","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271792","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-271792r1094968_rule","rule_id":"SV-271792","rule_version":"OL09-00-002530","rule_title":"OL 9 /boot/grub2/grub.cfg file must be group-owned by root.","fix_text":"Change the group of the file /boot/grub2/grub.cfg to root by running the following command:\n\n$ sudo chgrp root /boot/grub2/grub.cfg","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 configures the group ownership of the \"/boot/grub2/grub.cfg\" file with the following command:\n\n$ sudo stat -c \"%G %n\" /boot/grub2/grub.cfg \nroot /boot/grub2/grub.cfg\n\nIf \"/boot/grub2/grub.cfg\" file does not have a group owner of \"root\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The \"root\" group is a highly privileged group. The group-owner of this file should not have any access privileges.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"7935","uuid":"f4adedfa-819e-4b27-9651-149ff73eb981","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 6BA326D98AF1BE66B82B97DD92C1D8A64B3C7C51\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'OL 9 /boot/grub2/grub.cfg file must be group-owned by root.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271793","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271793","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271793","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-271793r1092605_rule","rule_id":"SV-271793","rule_version":"OL09-00-002531","rule_title":"OL 9 /boot/grub2/grub.cfg file must be owned by root.","fix_text":"Change the owner of the file /boot/grub2/grub.cfg to root by running the following command:\n\n$ sudo chown root /boot/grub2/grub.cfg","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 configures ownership of the \"/boot/grub2/grub.cfg\" file with the following command:\n\n$ sudo stat -c \"%U %n\" /boot/grub2/grub.cfg \nroot /boot/grub2/grub.cfg \n\nIf \"/boot/grub2/grub.cfg\" file does not have an owner of \"root\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The \"/boot/grub2/grub.cfg\" file stores sensitive system configuration. Protection of this file is critical for system security.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"9427","uuid":"57367b14-017f-4e9d-81bb-0f22b15d58d2","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: ACCA732C5B370716FCCFCC1C0628117EB5071026\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'OL 9 /boot/grub2/grub.cfg file must be owned by root.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271794","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271794","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271794","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-271794r1092094_rule","rule_id":"SV-271794","rule_version":"OL09-00-002532","rule_title":"OL 9 /etc/group file must be group-owned by root.","fix_text":"Change the group of the file /etc/group to root by running the following command:\n\n$ sudo chgrp root /etc/group","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 configures group ownership of the \"/etc/group\" file with the following command:\n\n$ stat -c \"%G %n\" /etc/group \nroot /etc/group\n\nIf \"/etc/group\" file does not have a group owner of \"root\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The \"/etc/group\" file contains information regarding groups that are configured on the system. Protection of this file is important for system security.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"7126","uuid":"508bf1e2-d98f-4e88-a12e-27bd76a500b6","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 33EA4B66A6AE0E3405A63F3C820364380903FA8B\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'OL 9 /etc/group file must be group-owned by root.' is not present or not in use on this the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271795","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271795","title":"SRG-OS-00