afinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: BC517932D6B21E567F8C9144DCAE0DF3FE32061A\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'OL 9 /etc/shadow- file must have mode 0000 or less permissive to prevent unauthorized access.' matches the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271817","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271817","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271817","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-271817r1092163_rule","rule_id":"SV-271817","rule_version":"OL09-00-002555","rule_title":"OL 9 /etc/shadow file must have mode 0000 to prevent unauthorized access.","fix_text":"Change the mode of the file \"/etc/shadow\" to \"0000\" by running the following command:\n\n$ sudo chmod 0000 /etc/shadow","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 configures the \"/etc/shadow\" file to have a mode of \"0000\" with the following command:\n\n$ stat -c \"%a %n\" /etc/shadow\n0 /etc/shadow\n\nIf a value of \"0\" is not returned, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The \"/etc/shadow\" file contains the list of local system accounts and stores password hashes. Protection of this file is critical for system security. Failure to give ownership of this file to root provides the designated owner with access to sensitive information, which could weaken the system security posture.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"7102","uuid":"6b716bcd-a6c8-4e1e-a963-3e4f3bea43b9","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 06F7F98AC0089C52CD8A9B8F7C745BEF08836E1E\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'OL 9 /etc/shadow file must have mode 0000 to prevent unauthorized access.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271818","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271818","title":"SRG-OS-000206-GPOS-00084","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271818","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000206-GPOS-00084","rule_id_src":"SV-271818r1092166_rule","rule_id":"SV-271818","rule_version":"OL09-00-002560","rule_title":"OL 9 /var/log directory must be group-owned by root.","fix_text":"Configure the group owner of the directory \"/var/log\" to \"root\" by running the following command:\n\n$ sudo chgrp root /var/log","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 configures the \"/var/log\" directory to be group-owned by root with the following command:\n\n$ ls -ld /var/log\ndrwxr-xr-x. 16 root root 4096 July 11 11:34 /var/log\n\nIf \"/var/log\" does not have a group owner of \"root\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Only authorized personnel should be aware of errors and the details of the errors. Error messages are an indicator of an organization's operational state or can identify the OL 9 system or platform. Additionally, personally identifiable information (PII) and operational information must not be revealed through error messages to unauthorized personnel or their designated representatives.\n\nThe structure and content of error messages must be carefully considered by the organization and development team. The extent to which the information system is able to identify and handle error conditions is guided by organizational policy and operational requirements.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001314"],"reference_identifier":"1338","uuid":"5ed4f454-28a6-47f7-8b3d-4d740af8790c","stig_uuid":"9f4b762d-8654-4328-882b-f95f4ce5315e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-OracleLinux9_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 58498FDCCC085C692536868369C85F6049CA708F\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'OL 9 /var/log directory must be group-owned by root.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Oracle Linux 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271819","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271819","title":"SRG-OS-000206-GPOS-00084","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271819","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000206-GPOS-00084","rule_id_src":"SV-271819r1092169_rule","rule_id":"SV-271819","rule_version":"OL09-00-002561","rule_title":"OL 9 /var/log directory must be owned by root.","fix_text":"Configure the owner of the directory \"/var/log\" to \"root\" by running the following command:\n\n$ sudo chown root /var/log","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that OL 9 configures the \"/var/log\" directory to be owned by root with the following command:\n\n$ ls -ld /var/log\ndrwxr-xr-x. 16 root root 4096 July 11 11:34 /var/log\n\nIf \"/var/log\" does not have an owner of \"root\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Oracle_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Only authorized personnel should be aware of errors and the details of the errors. Error messages are an indicator of an organization's operational state or can identify the OL 9 system or platform. Additionally, personally identifiable information (PII) and operational information must